i>Nepal visa (apply upon arrival)</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>Personal &amp; trek expenses (including hot shower, drinking water, battery charging)</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss, theft and damages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '15', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 1500.00, 1400.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 10, 1, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2016-07-04 12:49:52', '2016-07-27 11:59:56', '2016-07-27 11:59:56'),
(33, 13, 1, '21 Days Annapurna Circuit Trek', '21-days-annapurna-circuit-trek', '21 Days Annapurna Circuit Trek', '21 Days Annapurna Circuit Trek', '21 Days Annapurna Circuit Trek', '<div>\r\n<p>Annapurna, attracts the largest number of trekkers in Nepal. Here you will find everything the Himalayas have to offer, accessible along a selection of well-maintained trails that snake in and around the 55-kilometre Annapurna massif, separated from the gargantuan Dhaulagiri (8167m) by the Kaligandaki, the deepest gorge in the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most trekkers will have heard of the legendary Annapurna Circuit. But if the lung-busting slog over the 5416m Thorung pass doesn&rsquo;t suit you, there are many other trails that offer superlative panoramas and the cultural traditions of a whole spectrum of ethnicities. And though roads are bringing change to the region, new trails are being blazed for the faithful. Up north at the border with China, the mystique of the walled city of Lo Manthang remains intact. Even in Nepal&rsquo;s most trekked places, a trail less travelled is never far away.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n', '<p>Day 1: Arrive Kathmandu<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 2: Kathmandu to Besisahar to Khudi (7 hrs drive)<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 3: Khudi to Bahundanda<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 4: Bahundanda - Chamje &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 5: Chamje - Dharapani &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 6: Dharapani - Koto &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 7: Koto - Pisang &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 8: Pisang - Manang<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 9: Manang<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 10: Manang - Yak Kharka &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 11: Yak Kharka - Thorong Phedi &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 12: Thorong Phedi&nbsp; - Thorong La (5416m) - Muktinath &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 13: Muktinath - Marpha &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 14: Marpha &ndash; Ghasa<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 15: Ghasa &ndash; Tatopani<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 16: Tatopani &ndash; Chitre<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 17: Chitre &ndash; Ghorepani<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 18: Ghorepani &ndash; Poonhill &ndash;&nbsp; Ulleri - Tirkhedhunga<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 19: Tirkhedhunga &ndash; Birethanti - Pokhara<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 20: Pokhara - Kathmandu<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 21: Kathmandu &ndash; Final Departure</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>City</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Private A/C transportation including airport transfer</li>\r\n	<li>Personal English speaking tour guide</li>\r\n	<li>Hotel accommodation</li>\r\n	<li>Meals as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Entrance fees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Trek&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>English speaking trekking guide (Assistant guide included for 4 and above persons)</li>\r\n	<li>Porter (1 porter to every 2 trekkers, each trekker&rsquo;s bag max 15kg)</li>\r\n	<li>Insurance for trekking crew</li>\r\n	<li>Lodge accommodation</li>\r\n	<li>Sleeping bag with fleece inner liner</li>\r\n	<li>Trek permit and national park fees</li>\r\n	<li>1 trekking map per trekker (provided in Nepal)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Nepal visa (apply upon arrival)</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>Personal &amp; trek expenses (including hot shower, drinking water, battery charging)</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss, theft and damages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '22', 'Raman Maharjan', NULL, '3 star hotel', NULL, 2, 4800, NULL, 'Sep - Dec', NULL, 1800.00, 1700.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, 1, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2016-07-04 13:00:59', '2016-07-27 11:58:42', '2016-07-27 11:58:42'),
(34, 13, 1, '17 Days Mystical Upper Mustang Trek', '17-days-mystical-upper-mustang-trek', '17 Days Mystical Upper Mustang Trek', '17 Days Mystical Upper Mustang Trek', '17 Days Mystical Upper Mustang Trek', '<p>The Upper Mustang trek brings you into the hidden world of the old Buddhist kingdom of Mustang, also called Lo. Lo used to be part of the Tibetan empire and is therefore closely tied&nbsp;to Tibet in culture, language and geography.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>The regions isolation from the outside world has contributed to a highly preserved Tibetan culture and unspoiled nature.&nbsp;Mustang lies in the rain shadow of the Dhaulagiri massif creating a ruggedly arid land surrounded by rocks in all kind of colors and impressive&nbsp;formations. This barren landscape is dotted with settlements of white washed houses, barley fields and chortens festooned with prayer flags which add a splash of color to the landscape.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The trail follows the ancient salt caravan route through which the people of Mustang traded Tibetan salt for grain from the lowlands. The goal of the Upper Mustang trek is the capital of Upper Mustang, Lo Manthang. From the pass Lo La (3950 m) you can see the walled medieval capital in the distance, the white-washed 6-meter tall wall sticking out in sharp contrast to the barren landscape.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n', '<p>Day 1: Arrive Kathmandu<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 2: Kathmandu - Pokhara<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 3: Pokhara-Jomsom flight - trek to Kagbeni<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 4: Kagbeni - Chele<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 5: Chele to Syanbochen [3475m/11,398ft]: 6-7 hrs<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 6: Syanbochen -Ghaymi<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 7: Ghaymi to Charang<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 8: Charang to Lo-Mangthang (3700m/12,136ft): 5-6 hrs<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 9: Explore Lo-Mangthang<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 10: Lo-Mangthang -Dhakmar [3810 m/12,500ft]: 6-7 hrs<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 11: Dhakmar -Ghiling<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 12: Ghiling-Chhusang<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 13: Chhusang-Kagbeni<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 14: Kagbeni - Jomsom &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 15: Jomsom - Pokhara - Kathmandu<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 16: Kathmandu<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 17: Kathmandu &ndash; Final Departure</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>City</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Private A/C transportation including airport transfer</li>\r\n	<li>2 way domestic flight with taxes (Jomsom &ndash; Pokhara-Jomosom)</li>\r\n	<li>1 way domestic flight with taxes (Pokhara &ndash; Kathmandu)</li>\r\n	<li>Personal English speaking tour guide</li>\r\n	<li>Hotel accommodation</li>\r\n	<li>Meals as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Entrance fees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Trek&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>English speaking trekking guide (Assistant guide included for 4 and above persons)</li>\r\n	<li>Special Mustang Permit (USD500 per pax for 10 Days)</li>\r\n	<li>Porter (1 porter to every 2 trekkers, each trekker&rsquo;s bag max 15kg)</li>\r\n	<li>Insurance for trekking crew</li>\r\n	<li>Lodge accommodation</li>\r\n	<li>Sleeping bag with fleece inner liner</li>\r\n	<li>Trek permit and national park fees</li>\r\n	<li>1 trekking map per trekker (provided in Nepal)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Nepal visa (apply upon arrival)</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>Personal &amp; trek expenses (including hot shower, drinking water, battery charging)</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss, theft and damages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '18', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 2450.00, 2350.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3, 1, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2016-07-04 13:07:04', '2016-07-27 11:58:56', '2016-07-27 11:58:56'),
(35, 13, 1, '10 Days Ghorepani Poonhill Trek', '10-days-ghorepani-poonhill-trek', '10 Days Ghorepani Poonhill Trek', '10 Days Ghorepani Poonhill Trek', '10 Days Ghorepani Poonhill Trek', '<p>At 3,210 meters, the Poon Hill sunrise view of the snowy rugged Annapurna Himalaya range, was worth every grueling step it took to get there!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Having the Himalayas close up, literally almost in my face, was a breathtaking sight!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The <strong>Ghorepani Poon Hill trek</strong> is a 8-9 days hike in the Annapurna mountain range in Nepal.&nbsp;It takes a moderate level of fitness to complete, and the max elevation is 3,210 meters (so there&rsquo;s no real risk of altitude sickness). Pokhara is the closest main access city to begin treks into the Annapurna range.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For the first part of this guide I&rsquo;ll share our itinerary of what we did and where we hiked each day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then below the day overviews you&rsquo;ll find all the information about how we prepared and arranged the trek, including costs and everything we spent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We did the Ghorepani Poon Hill trek in mid-March 2013, which is low season, and it was still quite cold (probably got down a little below freezing when we reached Ghorepani). Ghorepani Poon Hill Trek can be done year round, but in the thick of winter there might be quite a lot of snow and ice on the trail.</p>\r\n', '<p>Day 1: Arrive Kathmandu<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 2: Kathmandu &ndash; Pokhara - Birethanti<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 3: Birethanti - Ulleri<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nDay 4: Ulleri - Ghorepani<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 5: Ghorepani &ndash; Poonhill - Tadapani<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 6: Tadapani - Ghandrung<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 7: Ghandrung &ndash; Birethanti - Pokhara<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 8: Pokhara - Kathmandu<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 9: Kathmandu<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 10: Kathmandu &ndash; Final Departure</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>City</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Private A/C transportation including airport transfer</li>\r\n	<li>Personal English speaking tour guide</li>\r\n	<li>Hotel accommodation</li>\r\n	<li>Meals as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Entrance fees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Trek&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>English speaking trekking guide (Assistant guide included for 8 and above persons)</li>\r\n	<li>Porter (1 porter to every 2 trekkers, each trekker&rsquo;s bag max 15kg)</li>\r\n	<li>Insurance for trekking crew</li>\r\n	<li>Lodge accommodation</li>\r\n	<li>Sleeping bag with fleece inner liner</li>\r\n	<li>Trek permit and national park fees</li>\r\n	<li>1 trekking map per trekker (provided in Nepal)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Nepal visa (apply upon arrival)</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>Personal &amp; trek expenses (including hot shower, drinking water, battery charging)</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss, theft and damages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '11', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 2000.00, 1000.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 9, 1, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2016-07-04 13:10:58', '2016-07-27 11:59:39', '2016-07-27 11:59:39'),
(36, 13, 1, '8 Days Panchase Trek with Nagarkot Tour', '8-days-panchase-trek-with-nagarkot-tour', '8 Days Panchase Trek with Nagarkot Tour', '8 Days Panchase Trek with Nagarkot Tour', '8 Days Panchase Trek with Nagarkot Tour', '<p>Panchase Trek 8 days 7 nights is one of newest trekking routes near Pokhara. The trail is less trodden thus making it ideal for those who prefer less crowded area. There are very few hotels along the route however home stay facilities are easily available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Panchase Trek 3 days 2 nights takes you all the way to the Panchase peak(2517m). The trekking route passes through Dhampus village, perhaps the most photographed destination in Nepal. Although this is a short trek the trek offers a milieu of natural forests, mountain views and typical Nepali villages and traditional hospitality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You could also spot abundance of wild marihuana plants growing along the trail of Panchase Trek.</p>\r\n', '<p>Day 1: Arrive Kathmandu<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 2: Kathmandu - Pokhara<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 3: Pokhara- Nele Kharka<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 4: Nele Kharka &ndash; Panchase<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 5: Panchase-Naudanda-Pokhara<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 6: Pokhara &ndash; Kathmandu &ndash; Nagarkot &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 7: Nagarkot &ndash; Kathmandu<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 8: Kathmandu &ndash; Final Departure</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>City</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Private A/C transportation including airport transfer</li>\r\n	<li>Personal English speaking tour guide</li>\r\n	<li>Hotel accommodation</li>\r\n	<li>Meals as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Entrance fees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Trek&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>English speaking trekking guide (Assistant guide)</li>\r\n	<li>Complete 4 days camping trek arrangement</li>\r\n	<li>Equipment: Two man tents, Sleeping bag with fleece inner liner, Toilet tents and necessary kitchen equipment</li>\r\n	<li>Manpower: Trekking guide, assistance guide, cook, kitchen boys and helpers and require porters</li>\r\n	<li>Insurance for trekking crew</li>\r\n	<li>Lodge accommodation</li>\r\n	<li>Sleeping bag with fleece inner liner</li>\r\n	<li>Trek permit and national park fees</li>\r\n	<li>1 Trekking Map per trekker (provided in Nepal)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Nepal visa (apply upon arrival)</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>Personal &amp; trek expenses (including hot shower, drinking water, battery charging)</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss, theft and damages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '9', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 1000.00, 900.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4, 1, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2016-07-04 13:31:37', '2016-07-27 11:59:04', '2016-07-27 11:59:04'),
(37, 13, 1, '25 Days Naar Phu Trek with Thorung-La', '25-days-naar-phu-trek-with-thorung-la', '25 Days Naar Phu Trek with Thorung-La', '25 Days Naar Phu Trek with Thorung-La', '25 Days Naar Phu Trek with Thorung-La', '<p>25 Days Naar Phu Trek with Thorung-La</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The <strong>Nar Phu valley</strong> is a trek that combines remote villages of Nar and Phu, narrow canyons, lovely forests, amazing rock formations, yaks, Monasteries,<strong> </strong>Kang La Pass and unique Himalayan cultures. You should have physically fitness to do this trek.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This trek starts from <strong>Chamje</strong> after 9 hours driving from Kathmandu. We hike same trail as Annapurna circuit trek. After arriving to Koto, we cross the bridge leading over the Marshyangdi River to the steep portals of the Nar Phu valley is easily missed, but although the entrance is narrow and forested, the valley system above opens up to a huge expanse of high snow-peaks, ancient villages and high altitude grazing settlements. Trekkers until late 2002, very few westerners have explored these virtually untouched villages or climbed the many 7000m peaks surrounding it. We will venture into this remote region of Nar Phu valley. Buddhist pilgrims from around Nepal might accompany us up to Phu to visit the renowned Tashi Lhakhang Gompa and receive a blessing from Lama Karma Sonam Rimpoche. Along with spending plenty of time at these colorful and timeless villages, we explore the high alpine valleys above Phu. The <strong>Kang La (5315m) pass</strong> is amazing. We may enjoy mountains view like annapurna II, Gangapurna, Tilicho peak then join to manang for annapurna circuit trek. The village of Manang (3,500m/11483feet) marks the beginning of the next stage. You will come back from Manang to Chame from where you can drive back to Kathmandu by public Jeep. If you have time, you can also continue to Jomsom via Thorong La Pass.</p>\r\n', '<p>Day 1: Arrive Kathmandu<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 2: Kathmandu to Besisahar to Khudi (6 hrs drive)<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 3: Khudi to Bahundanda<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 4: Bahundanda - Chamje &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 5: Chamje - Dharapani &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 6: Dharapani - Koto &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 7: Koto - Pisang &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 8: Koto-Singenge Dharmasala<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 9: Dharmasala- Kyang<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 10: Kyang- Phu<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 11: Phu<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\nDay 12: Phu-Junam<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 13: Junam &ndash;Naar Village<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 14: Naar Village<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 15: Naar Village-Kang La Pass (5306m)-Nawal (3660m)<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 16: Nawal - Manang<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 17: Manang<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 18: Manang - Yak Kharka &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 19: Yak Kharka - Thorong Phedi &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 20: Thorong Phedi&nbsp; - Thorong La (5416m) - Muktinath &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 21: Muktinath - Jomsom &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 22: Jomsom - Pokhara<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 23: Pokhara - Kathmandu<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 24: Kathmandu<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 25: Kathmandu &ndash; Final Departure</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>City</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Private A/C transportation including airport transfer</li>\r\n	<li>1 way domestic flight with taxes (Jomsom &ndash; Pokhara)</li>\r\n	<li>Personal English speaking tour guide</li>\r\n	<li>Hotel accommodation</li>\r\n	<li>Meals as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Entrance fees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Trek&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>English speaking trekking guide (Assistant guide included for 4 and above persons)</li>\r\n	<li>Naar Phu special permit fees</li>\r\n	<li>Manpower for camping trek cook, helper and require porter for camping with necessary camping equipment &nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Porter (1 porter to every 2 trekkers, each trekker&rsquo;s bag max 15kg)</li>\r\n	<li>Insurance for trekking