(39, 13, 1, '12 Days Annapurna BC Trek (Express)', '12-days-annapurna-bc-trek-express', '12 Days Annapurna BC Trek (Express)', '12 Days Annapurna BC Trek (Express)', '12 Days Annapurna BC Trek (Express)', '<p>The Annapurna Sanctuary region is blessed with countless mountain summits that will take your breath away just looking at them. &nbsp;The trail follows the deep valley cut by the Modi Khola river and its ancient glaciers. &nbsp;If you trek in spring you will get to walk through many kilometers of gorgeous rhododendron forests in full bloom. You then pass below the sacred mountain of Mount Machhapuchchhre, 6,993m, also known commonly as Fishtail for obvious reasons when you see it. &nbsp;You are certain to return home with at least 100 stunning photos of just this mountain alone. &nbsp;Its gorgeous ice-capped summit grabs your eye and tugs at your heart with every twist and turn of the trail.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The trek continues further up the valley before turning west into the vast natural amphitheater valley below the towering summit and rock wall of Annapurna South, 8,091m. &nbsp;Standing at Annapurna Base Camp will leave you awed by the might and beauty of Himalayan peaks that totally surround you. &nbsp;This is one of the most stunning vistas in the entire Himalaya Mountain range and something that you will remember for the rest of your life.</p>\r\n', '<p>Day 1: Arrive Kathmandu<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 2: Kathmandu &ndash; Pokhara - Birethanti<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 3: Birethanti - Ghandruk &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 4: Ghandruk - Chhomrong &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 5: Chhomrong - Dovan<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 6: Dovan - Deurali &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 7: Deurali - Machhapuchhre Base Camp<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 8: Machhapuchhare Base Camp &ndash; Annapurna Base Camp&nbsp; &ndash; Himalaya Hotel<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 9: Himalaya Hotel - Chhomrung &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 10: Chhomrung &ndash; Nayapul-Seulibazaar- Birethanti - Pokhara<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 11: Pokhara - Kathmandu<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 12: Kathmandu &ndash; Final Departure</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>City</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Private A/C transportation including airport transfer</li>\r\n	<li>Personal English speaking tour guide</li>\r\n	<li>Hotel accommodation</li>\r\n	<li>Meals as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Entrance fees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Trek</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>English speaking trekking guide (Assistant guide included for 8 and above persons)</li>\r\n	<li>Porter (1 porter to every 2 trekkers, each trekker&rsquo;s bag max 15kg)</li>\r\n	<li>Insurance for trekking crew</li>\r\n	<li>Lodge accommodation</li>\r\n	<li>Sleeping bag with fleece inner liner</li>\r\n	<li>Trek permit and national park fees</li>\r\n	<li>1 trekking map per trekker (provided in Nepal)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Nepal visa (apply upon arrival)</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>Personal &amp; trek expenses (including hot shower, drinking water, battery charging)</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss, theft and damages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '13', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 1200.00, 1100.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 7, 1, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2016-07-04 13:42:17', '2016-07-27 11:59:23', '2016-07-27 11:59:23'),
(40, 13, 4, '6 Days Essential Nepal Tour', '6-days-essential-nepal-tour', '6 Days Essential Nepal Tour', '6 Days Essential Nepal Tour', '6 Days Essential Nepal Tour', '<p>Nepal is home to eight of the world&#39;s ten highest peaks including Mount Everest on the border with Tibet. With no less than ten natural and cultural UNESCO World Heritage Sites Nepal is as historically interesting as it is scenically breathtaking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The redspokes Nepal cycling holiday offers a complete experience of this wonderful country&#39;s varied landscape and culture. Bicycling from the Kathmandu Valley you will travel over mountain passes and into the tropical plains of the Terai to explore the flora and fauna of Chitwan National Park. You will climb through traditional villages as the landscape soars towards the snow-capped peaks of the Himalayas. Nepal has long exerted a pull on the Western imagination. Join us on this exhilarating and memorable cycling adventure holiday and discover its wonders for yourself.</p>\r\n', '<p>Day 01: Arrive &ndash; KATHMANDU (D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 02: KATHMANDU-POKHARA (232KM) (B,L,D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 03: POKHARA-SARANGKOT-POKHARA (B,L,D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 04: POKHARA-KATHMANDU-NAGARKOT (200KM) (B,L,D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 05: NAGARKOT-KATHMANDU (B,L,D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 06: KATHMANDU &ndash; DEPARTURE (B)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>All the private A/C transportation including airport transfer</li>\r\n	<li>1 way Pokhara &ndash; Kathmandu domestic flight</li>\r\n	<li>All the city tour with English speaking tour guide</li>\r\n	<li>All the accommodation</li>\r\n	<li>All the meals as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>All the entrance fees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Nepal visa (apply upon arrival)</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li>All alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>All personal expenses</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss, theft and damages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '7', '', NULL, '',