(53, 13, 7, '5 Days Nepal Tour Kathmandu –Pokhara ', '5-days-nepal-tour-kathmandu-pokhara', '5 Days Nepal Tour Kathmandu –Pokhara ', '5 Days Nepal Tour Kathmandu –Pokhara ', '5 Days Nepal Tour Kathmandu –Pokhara ', '<p>The capital of Kathmandu offers stunning ancient architecture, colorful vibrant bazaars with the majestic snow-capped Himalayas as the backdrop. Pokhara is a lovely valley surrounded by the majestic Annapurnas. This tour is the best sampler of Nepal for those with limited time.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Day 01: Arrive &ndash; KATHMANDU (D)</strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival meet and transfer to hotel and briefing. After that visit Thamel, a popular tourist district in Kathmandu Valley and a bustling bazaar which offers a glimpse of Nepal&rsquo;s vibrant ethnic culture. Evening dinner<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 02: KATHMANDU&ndash;POKHARA (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nMorning meet and transfer to <strong>Pokhara</strong> (200km). The Annapurna and the famous Machhapucchare (Commonly known as Fishtail Mountain) tower over the tropical setting of Pokhara. Drive takes about 5 hours. This scenic drive will offer great view of local villages, jungle and rivers. Upon reaching Pokhara, check-in hotel. Afternoon an hour leisure <strong>boating at scenic Lake Fewa and visit Barahi Temple in the middle of the lake</strong>. Late afternoon enjoy walk around <strong>Lakeside Bazaar</strong> for some delightful shopping bargains.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 03: POKHARA-SARANGKOT-POKHARA (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nEarly morning, drive up to <strong>Sarangkot</strong> (1200m) sunrise view point for 30 minutes. Expect a very spectacular view of sunrise over the whole Annapurna range including the Machhapucchare of height close to 7000m. After sunrise, drive back to Pokhara for breakfast. After breakfast, visit <strong>Tibetan Refugees&rsquo; Camp, Devi&rsquo;s Fall and Mahadev Gupteswar Cave. </strong>Afternoon free at leisure around lakeside bazaar. Evening dinner.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 04: POKHARA&ndash;KATHMANDU (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast, drive to Kathmandu (1300m) about 5 hrs. Late afternoon leisure walk in Thamel, a popular tourist district in Kathmandu Valley and a bustling bazaar which offers a glimpse of Nepal&rsquo;s vibrant ethnic culture.<br />\r\nAfter that explore Asan Tol. It is one of the most well-known historical locations in the city and is famed for its bazaar, festival calendar and strategic location. The bazaar attracts shoppers from all over Kathmandu because of the tremendous variety of merchandise sold here, ranging from foodstuffs, spices and textiles to electronics and bullion. Asan is also one of the popular tourist spots in the city because of its architectural sights and charming ambiance.<br />\r\nEvening enjoy a sumptuous traditional Nepalese Cuisine with Cultural Performance.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 05: KATHMANDU- DEPARTURE (B) </strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast check out and city tour to Kathmandu Durbar Square, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and if you are lucky, you will get a glimpse of the famous Kumari, the world&rsquo;s only living Goddess. This complex of palaces, courtyards and temples like Hanumandhoka Palace, Kumari Ghar (Abode of the Living Goddess), Taleju temple, built between the 12th and 18th centuries, used to be the seat of the ancient Malla Kings of Kathmandu. After that transfer to airport for departure according to your flight schedule.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note: </strong><br />\r\n&bull; This is a private trip arrangements<br />\r\n&bull; Cost based on minimum 2 pax traveling<br />\r\n&bull; Single supplement additional SGD150</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>All private transportation including airport transfer as per above itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>All the city tour with English speaking tour guide</li>\r\n	<li>All the accommodation on twin sharing room basis as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>All the meals as per above itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>All the entrance fees for sightseeing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>International air ticket with all the taxes</li>\r\n	<li>Nepal Visa (apply upon arrival)</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li>All alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>Personal clothing</li>\r\n	<li>Laundry</li>\r\n	<li>Telephone bills</li>\r\n	<li>All personal expenses</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss, theft and damages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips for guide and driver</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '5', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 600.00, 650.00, 'Kathmandu', 'Kathmandu', 'package_banner_1469607754.jpg', NULL, 1, 1, 1, '1', '0', '1', '2016-07-27 12:21:45', '2016-08-08 16:36:44', NULL),
(54, 13, 1, '08 Days Nepal Adventure Ghorepani/Poonhill Trek', '08-days-nepal-adventure-ghorepani-poonhill-trek', '08 DAYS NEPAL ADVENTURE GHOREPANI/POONHILL TREK ', '08 DAYS NEPAL ADVENTURE GHOREPANI/POONHILL TREK ', '08 DAYS NEPAL ADVENTURE GHOREPANI/POONHILL TREK ', '<p>Ghorepani Poonhill trek is a colorful short foray into the Annapurna region. At the climax of this trek you will climb Poon Hill at dawn to enjoy one of the most spectacular mountains on Earth. As the sun touches the snow-capped summits, the Himalayan giants along with a maze of other peaks, slowly begin to appear, like magic, before your eyes.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Day 01: ARRIVE - KATHMANDU (D)</strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival, meet and transfer to hotel. Welcome drinks followed by briefing and begin city tour to <strong>Swayambhunath </strong>Stupa, where you can see the whole Kathmandu valley with sunset view. The Stupa, listed as a World Heritage Site, is one of the holiest Buddhist sites in Nepal and its establishment is linked to the creation of the Kathmandu Valley out of a primordial lake.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Evening leisure walk in <strong>Thamel,</strong> a popular tourist district in Kathmandu Valley (1300M) and a bustling bazaar which offers a glimpse of Nepal&rsquo;s vibrant ethnic culture. &ndash; Overnight at Hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 02: KATHMANDU-POKHARA-BIRETHANTI (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast take drive to Birethanti via Pokhara, drive will takes about 7 hours. Begin short trek about 30 min to Birethanti.&nbsp; Overnight at lodge.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 03: BIRETHANTI- ULLERI</strong> <strong>(1960m)</strong> <strong>(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek.&nbsp; You will ascend stone-cut steps made by ancients of old to access villages from one to another.&nbsp; As you climb higher, the panoramic view of villages dots the land below.&nbsp; After Lunch will be steep climb up hill it will take about 2 and half hours.&nbsp; Overnight at lodge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 04</strong>: <strong>ULLERI-GHOREPANI</strong> <strong>(2860m)</strong> <strong>(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nToday, the trail continues to ascend, albeit more gently, through fine forest of oak and rhododendron.&nbsp; Ghorepani (2855 m) means &ldquo;horse-water&rdquo; in Nepalese.&nbsp; Indeed, along the whole trek, you probably have seen caravans of packed mules adorned beautifully thronging the high roads.&nbsp; Nestled on top of the mountain, this village is shrouded with clouds and offers the magnificient view of Dhaulagiri and Annapurna range. Overnight at lodge</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 05: GHOREPANI-POONHILL-TADAPANI </strong><strong>(2603m)</strong> <strong>(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nEarly morning climb to <strong>Poon Hill (3015 m)</strong> take about 1 hour 30 minute. This high point offers a <strong>panoramic 360 degrees Annapurna range</strong>, <strong>Fishtail, Dhulagiri and Nilgiri Mountain</strong> around you.&nbsp; Your climb will be well-timed such that you will be able to watch <strong>sunrise</strong> approaching the mountains.&nbsp; It will be a memorable experience to relish; especially catching the sight of the distant snow peaks bathed in a coat of gold. After spending morning at the Poonhill then trek back to Ghorepani for breakfast. After breakfast trek to Tadapnai trek about 5 hours -over night Lodge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 06:&nbsp; TADAPANI- -GHANDRUNG- BIRETHANTI-POKHARA (B,L,D)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After breakfast gradual flat and down hill trek all the way to Ghandrung takes about 3 hours.&nbsp; You will reach for lunch. Ghandrung is modern Gurung village. Also popular as &ldquo;Gurkha&rdquo; village as most the Gurkha&rsquo;s are from this village. After luch</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Continue trek down hill about 3 hours ending point of trek at Birethanti. Transfer back to <strong>Pokhara.</strong> Upon arrival check-in hotel. Evening some delightful shopping around the lake side bazaar. Evening Dinner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 07: </strong><strong>POKHARA- KATHMANDU</strong> <strong>(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast drive to Kathmandu. Drive will takes about 5 hrs. Lunch will be on the way. Upon reaching Kathmandu city tour visit <strong>Kathmandu Durbar Square, </strong>a UNESCO World Heritage Site,<strong> </strong>and if you are lucky, you will get a glimpse of the famous <strong>Kumari, the world&rsquo;s only living Goddess.</strong> This complex of palaces, courtyards and temples like <strong>Hanumandhoka Palace, Kumari Ghar</strong> (Abode of the Living Goddess), <strong>Taleju temple</strong>, <strong>Bhagwati Temple, Bhairawa Temple</strong> built between the 12th and 18th centuries, used to be the seat of the ancient Malla Kings of Kathmandu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the tour transfer to hotel and &nbsp;check in hotel. Late afternoon last minute shopping around Thamel. Evening enjoy a sumptuous traditional <strong>Nepalese Cuisine</strong> with <strong>Cultural Performance</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 08: KATHMANDU &ndash; Final Departure (B)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast,&nbsp; city tour visit <strong>Bouddhanath Stupa</strong>, one of the world&rsquo;s largest Stupa built in the fifth century AD. It looms 36 meters high and presents one of the most fascinating specimens of Stupa design with hundreds of prayer wheels and 108 small images of Buddha all around. All the Buddhist throng to this Stupa to take part in the sacred rituals during the Buddhist festivals. Transfer back to hotel.&nbsp; After that transfer to airport to fly out according to the flight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note: </strong><br />\r\n&bull; This is a private trip arrangements<br />\r\n&bull; Cost based on minimum 2 pax traveling<br />\r\n&bull; Single room supplement additional SGD150</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>All Transportation by Private vehicle including airport transfer as per above itinerary.</li>\r\n	<li>3 nights accommodation in Kathmandu and Pokhara as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>All the meals as per above itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Complete 5 days lodge trek arrangement with:</li>\r\n	<li>Equipment: Sleeping bag with fleece inner liner</li>\r\n	<li>Manpower: head guide and required porter.</li>\r\n	<li>Miscellaneous: National park fees , trekking staff and porter insurance</li>\r\n	<li>City tour with English speaking tour guide</li>\r\n	<li>All the entrance fees for places of visit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Return air ticket with all the taxes</li>\r\n	<li>Visa fee (USD25) &ndash; apply upon arrival</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li>All alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>Personal clothing</li>\r\n	<li>Laundry</li>\r\n	<li>Telephone bills</li>\r\n	<li>All personal expenses</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss, theft and damages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '8', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 700.00, 650.00, 'Kathmandu', 'Kathmandu', 'package_banner_1469609206.jpg', NULL, 2, 1, 1, '1', '0', '1', '2016-07-27 12:46:46', '2016-08-08 16:36:44', NULL),
(55, 13, 2, '08 Days Nepal White Water Rafting, National Park with Paragliding', '08-days-nepal-white-water-rafting-national-park-with-paragliding', '08 Days Nepal White Water Rafting, National Park with Paragliding', '08 Days Nepal White Water Rafting, National Park with Paragliding', '08 Days Nepal White Water Rafting, National Park with Paragliding', '<p>A classic tour to Nepal with the thrill of rafting in the Himalaya Glacier waters. Great for those seeking a mild outdoor experience minus the challenge.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Day 01: Arrive &ndash; KATHMANDU (D)</strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival meet and transfer to hotel. Briefing and welcome drink. Late afternoon walking tour around Thamel, a popular tourist district in Kathmandu Valley and a bustling bazaar which offers a glimpse of Nepal&rsquo;s vibrant ethnic culture. Evening Dinner.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 02: KATHMANDU &ndash;RAFTING- CHITWAN NATIONAL PARK (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast enjoy a two hour scenic drive along Trisuli River to the Rafting starting point. Meet up with Rafting crew who will provide river safety briefing and demonstrate rafting equipment. Have fun whitewater rafting in the great outdoors for about three hours. At the end point, change into dry clothing and enjoy a specially packed picnic lunch.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter that drive to Chitwan National Park, listed on the UNESCO World Heritage Site. It is the first national park of Nepal established in 1973 to preserve a unique ecosystem significantly valuable to the whole world. The park covering a pristine area of 932 sq. km is situated in the subtropical inner Terai lowlands of southern central part of Nepal. Drive takes about 1 and half hours. Upon arrival meet and transfer to Jungle Lodge. Welcome drinks and briefing. Late afternoon short walk in the Tharu Village to take in the scenery of the rustic countryside. Evening dinner and Cultural Performance at the lodge.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 03: CHITWAN NATIONAL PARK (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast long boat Canoe in Rapati River where you can see the crocodile resting at the river bank. After that visit Elephant Breeding Center. After lunch, some rest time and enjoy the nature on an Elephant Back Ride. You may come across endangered species of mammals such as the one-horned Rhinoceros. Other wild animals found in the park are hog deer, barking deer, sloth bear, rhesus monkey etc. Evening dinner.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 04: CHITWAN NATIONAL PARK &ndash; POKHARA (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast transfer to Pokhara. The Annapurna and the famous Machhapucchare (Commonly known as Fishtail Mountain) tower over the tropical setting of Pokhara. Drive takes about four and half hours. Upon arrival check-in to hotel. Afternoon city tour to Tibetan Refugees&rsquo; Camp, Devi&rsquo;s Fall and Mahadev Gupteswar Cave. Late afternoon an hour leisure boating at scenic Lake Fewa and visit Barahi Temple in the middle of the lake. Evening enjoy walk around Lakeside Bazaar for some delightful shopping bargains followed by dinner.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 05: POKHARA &ndash; SARANGKOT &ndash; POKHARA (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nEarly morning, drive up to Sarangkot (1200m) sunrise view point for 30 minutes. Expect a very spectacular view of sunrise over the whole Annapurna range including the Machhapucchare of height close to 7000m. After sunrise, drive back to Pokhara for breakfast.<br />\r\nAfter breakfast, transfer to Paragliding take off point. This is one of the most memorable &amp; life time experience where flying captain will take you on a one to one basis in this 40 min journey across the valleys. End of the flight landing Lakeside and drive back to hotel. Afternoon free time to enjoy walking around Lakeside and shopping. Evening dinner.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 06: POKHARA &ndash; KATHMANDU &ndash; NAGARKOT (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast, drive to Nagarkot via Kathmandu. sunrise and sunset from this popular hill resort present you the breathtaking view of the Eastern Himalayan Range including Mt. Everest which can be seen on a clear day. It is a scenic drive with lots of lovely quaint little houses and paddy fields which takes about one and half hours. Drive takes about 7 hours. Lunch will be on the way. Upon arrival, check in Resort. Enjoy a relaxing short nature walk and catch the gorgeous sunset. Evening dinner.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 07: NAGARKOT&nbsp; &ndash; KATHMANDU (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAwake in the morning to the cold but stunningly spectacular sunrise over Nagarkot Hill. The first ray of the sun firing the peak glimmering red, slowly lighting the Himalaya range. Mt Everest in the far east and Langtang and the Dhaulagiri peak in the west.<br />\r\nAfter breakfast, drive back to Kathmandu. On the way, visit Kathmandu Durbar Square, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and if you are lucky, you will get a glimpse of the famous Kumari, the world&rsquo;s only living Goddess. This complex of palaces, courtyards and temples like Hanumandhoka Palace, Kumari Ghar (Abode of the Living Goddess), Taleju temple, built between the 12th and 18th centuries, used to be the seat of the ancient Malla Kings of Kathmandu. Lunch in the city centre.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter lunch visit Bouddhanath Stupa, one of the world&rsquo;s largest Stupa built in the fifth century AD. It looms 36 meters high and presents one of the most fascinating specimens of stupa design with hundreds of prayer wheels and 108 small images of Buddha all around. Late afternoon free to explore Asan Tol, the colourful local market area and shopping. Evening enjoy a sumptuous traditional Nepalese Cuisine with Cultural Performance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 08: KATHMANDU &ndash; DEPARTURE (B)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast transfer to Airport for fly out according to your flight schedule.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Note:</strong><br />\r\n&bull; Rating and tour will be conducted on private group basis. (No group joining)<br />\r\n&bull; Single room supplement additional cost SGD150<br />\r\n&bull; Minimum 2 pax to travel</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>All the private transportation including airport transfer as per above itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>All the city tour with English speaking guide</li>\r\n	<li>40 min Paragliding tandem flight with all the taxes</li>\r\n	<li>All the accommodation on twin or triple sharing basis</li>\r\n	<li>All the meals as per above itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>3 Days 2 night Chitwan National park package including all the jungle activities &amp; fees</li>\r\n	<li>1 night Nagarkot resort package</li>\r\n	<li>Whitewater Rafting with equipment and lunch</li>\r\n	<li>All the entrance fees for the places</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Return international airfare including taxes</li>\r\n	<li>Nepal Visa USD25 ( apply upon arrival)</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li>All alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>Personal clothing</li>\r\n	<li>Laundry</li>\r\n	<li>Telephone bills</li>\r\n	<li>All personal expenses</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss, theft and damages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips for driver and guide</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '8', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 1500.00, 1100.00, 'Kathmandu', 'Nagarkot', 'package_banner_1469610202.jpg', NULL, 10, 1, 1, '1', '0', '1', '2016-07-27 13:03:22', '2016-08-08 16:37:40', NULL),
(56, 13, 1, '10 Days Nepal Everest Panorama Trek.', '10-days-nepal-everest-panorama-trek', '10 Days Nepal Everest Panorama Trek.', '10 Days Nepal Everest Panorama Trek.', '10 Days Nepal Everest Panorama Trek.', '<p>Trekking to base camp of the world&rsquo;s tallest peak, the Mt. Everest (8,848m) is a thrilling experience in itself. The views from almost anywhere on Kalapather of Everest, Lotse and Nuptse are spectacular.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Day 01: ARRIVE KATHMANDU (1300M) (D)</strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival meet and transfer to hotel. Briefing and welcome drink. Late afternoon leisure walk around Thamel. <strong>Thamel a popular tourist district in Kathmandu Valley and a bustling bazaar</strong> which offers a glimpse of Nepal&rsquo;s vibrant ethnic culture. Overnight at hotel.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 02: KATHMANDU-LUKLA- PHAKDING (2640M) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nEarly morning breakfast and transfer to airport and connect the flight to <strong>Lukla</strong>. This is 30min short flight. Upon reaching Lukla serve with hot tea and meet up with rest of the trek crew. After that start trek to Phakding. It will takes about 3 and half hrs. The trail will be gradual flat with up and down hill. Overnight at lodge&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 03: PHADKING-NAMCHE BAZAAR (3440M) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. The trail will be gradual flat till <strong>Monjo</strong>, it will takes about 2 and half hours. Group will stop for lunch. After lunch, continue trek to <strong>Jorsale</strong> about 40 min and after crossing bridge the trail will be up hill all the way to Namache. This will be the bit difficult part as it is up hill. It will take about 3 hrs. Upon reaching Namche check in lodge.&nbsp; Over night at lodge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 04: NAMCHE BAZAAR &ndash; REST DAY FOR ACCLIMATIZATION&nbsp; (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast short hike to <strong>Shyangbuche </strong>(3833m) it will takes about 1 hrs up hill. From this point you can see the Mt Everest with many more Mt views. After that back to Namche Bazaar for lunch. After lunch free and easy to explore Namche Bazaar. Overnight at loge.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 05: NAMCHE BAZAR &ndash;KHUMJUNG VILLAGE (3700 m) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nShort trek and trail will be gradual up and flat &ndash; takes about 3 hrs. After lunch tour around the Khumjung village and visit Monastery- Overnight at lodge.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 06: KHUMJUNG &ndash; JORSALA (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nTrek back via Namche &ndash; takes about 5 hrs &ndash; Overnight at Lodge.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 07: JORSALA &ndash; LUKLA (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nTrek back takes about 5 hours. Over night at Lodge.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 08: LUKLA &ndash; KATHMANDU (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast take a short flight back to Kathmandu. Upon arrival meet and transfer to hotel and rest and relax.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 09: KATHMANDU (B,L,D) &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast city tour visit Kathmandu Durbar Square, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and if you are lucky, you will get a glimpse of the famous Kumari, the world&rsquo;s only living Goddess. This complex of palaces, courtyards and temples like Hanumandhoka Palace, Kumari Ghar (Abode of the Living Goddess), Taleju temple, Bhagwati Temple, Bhairawa Temple built between the 12th and 18th centuries, used to be the seat of the ancient Malla Kings of Kathmandu.Lunch in the city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After lunch, visit&nbsp; Bouddhanath Stupa<em>, </em>one of the world&rsquo;s largest Stupa built in the fifth century AD. It looms 36 meters high and presents one of the most fascinating specimens of Stupa design with hundreds of prayer wheels and 108 small images of Buddha. Late afternoon free to explore Asan Tol, the colourful local market area and shopping. Evening enjoy a sumptuous <strong>Traditional Nepalese Cuisine with Cultural Performance</strong>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 10: KATHMANDU- DEPARTURE (B)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast, transfer to Airport for fly out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Land package with domestic flight: <strong>SGD1500 </strong>Per pax (Based on 3 star standard hotel)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong><br />\r\n1) All the trekking and tour will be conducted as private group basis<br />\r\n2) Single room supplement additional SGD250</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>All the necessary transport as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Return domestic airfare (Kathmandu &ndash; Lukla &ndash; Kathmandu) include taxes</li>\r\n	<li>Complete 06 days tea house trek arrangement</li>\r\n	<li>Equipment: Sleeping bag with fleece inner liner</li>\r\n	<li>Manpower: Trekking guide and porters</li>\r\n	<li>Meals: All meals as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Miscellaneous: National park fees, trekking guide and porters insurance</li>\r\n	<li>All the necessary ground transfers</li>\r\n	<li>Accommodation on 4 star hotel in Kathmandu</li>\r\n	<li>All the entrance fees for sightseeing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>International air ticket with taxes</li>\r\n	<li>Nepal Visa (USD25)</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li>All alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>Personal clothing</li>\r\n	<li>Laundry</li>\r\n	<li>Telephone bills</li>\r\n	<li>All personal expenses</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss, theft and damages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '10', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 1600.00, 1500.00, 'Kathmandu', 'Lukla', 'package_banner_1469610993.jpg', NULL, 3, 1, 1, '1', '0', '1', '2016-07-27 13:16:33', '2016-08-08 16:37:40', NULL);
