(57, 13, 1, '10 Days Nepal Langtang Trek ', '10-days-nepal-langtang-trek', '10 Days Nepal Langtang Trek ', '10 Days Nepal Langtang Trek ', '10 Days Nepal Langtang Trek ', '<p>The Langtang Valley is a beautiful alpine region situated to the North of Kathmandu bordering Tibet. It is popular due to its snow-covered peaks, a mild climate and friendly and hospitable inhabitants. The area was recognized as Nepal&#39;s first Himalayan National Park in 1971. The land of Tamangs, Langtang is rich in its age-old religious practices, language and costume. A journey to the Langtang valley offers an opportunity to explore the Tamang villages, climb small peaks and visit glaciers.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe trek is easily accessible from Kathmandu. The majestic mountains of Langtang Lirung (7246m) to the north, Gang Chhenpo (6388m) to the south and Dorje Lhakpa (6990m) to the east dominate the beautiful Langtang valley. The trek passes through lush forest and the unique settlements of diverse ethnic groups.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Day 01: ARRIVE - KATHMANDU (D)</strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival, meet and transfer to hotel. Welcome drinks followed by briefing. Late afternoon leisure walk in <strong>Thamel,</strong> a popular tourist district in Kathmandu Valley (1300M) and a bustling bazaar which offers a glimpse of Nepal&rsquo;s vibrant ethnic culture. &ndash; Overnight at Hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 02: <strong>KATHMANDU-DHUNCHE-SYABRU BENSI (1460M) (B,L,D)</strong></strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast drive to Dhunche. From Kathmandu, we take a 6 hr drive to Syabru Besi. After driving 15 km, we approach pristine villages on the banks of the river Trishuli. Here our trekking journey commences. We also get to view the enchanting panorama of the Himalaya, including the Ganesh Himal and the peaks of the Langtang region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 03: <strong>SYABRU BENSI-SHERPA GAON (2580m)</strong> (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. We traverse the ridge on Syabru Besi&rsquo;s main road and soon reach Ghopcha Khola. Terraced fields and dense forest with a variety of plant species like oaks, maple, alder and bamboo open up. Further on, the trail crosses a stream and a bridge. We pass by several small bhattis and reach Sherpa Goan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 04: SHERPA GAON-<strong>LAMA HOTEL (2700M)</strong> (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. Total trek will be about 5 hours. Morning&nbsp; one and half hours down the a little bit up and straight along the river, then straight one hour&nbsp; and just before Lama hotel little bit up trek. Overnight at Lodge</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 05: LAMA HOTEL &ndash;LANGTANG (3307m)</strong> <strong>(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. Total trek will be about 3 hours. Morning little bit up about half hour then one hour straight then half an hour climbing up, all the way up till Langtang. The day crossing some small villages will get some tea house and some jungle. Overnight at Lodge</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 06: LANGTANG -KYANJIN GOMPA</strong> (about 3649 m) <strong>(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. Total trek will be about 3 hours. Morning&nbsp; half an hour, little bit up then all the way straight till Kyangching, the day trek trail will be quite easy&nbsp; normally&nbsp; trekkers arrived in time for lunch. After lunch visit Monastery, cheese factory.<br />\r\nKyanning Gompa is the last village for Langtang region.&nbsp; Overnight at Lodge</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 07: KYANJIN GOMPA &ndash;LAMA HOTEL (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. Total trek will be about 5 hours. Overnight at Lodge</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 08: LAMA HOTEL<strong>-SYABRU BENSI</strong></strong><strong>(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. Total trek will be about 5 hours. Overnight at Lodge</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 09: SYABRU BENSI-DHUNCHE-KATHMANDU </strong><strong>(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast drive back to Kathmandu. Drive will takes about 7 hours. Check-in Hotel &ndash; Late afternoon free time for shopping. Evening enjoy a sumptuous traditional <strong>Nepalese Cuisine</strong> with <strong>Cultural Performance</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 10: KATHMANDU &ndash; Final Departure (B)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast check out and city tour visit <strong>Kathmandu Durbar Square</strong>, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and if you are lucky, you will get a glimpse of the<strong> famous Kumari, the world&rsquo;s only living Goddess</strong>. This complex of palaces, courtyards and temples like HanumandhokaPalace, KumariGhar (Abode of the Living Goddess), Taleju temple, built between the 12th and 18th centuries, used to be the seat of the ancient Malla Kings of Kathmandu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the tour transfer to Airport for fly out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Land Package cost: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SGD1150 Per pax (Based on 3 star standard hotel)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong><br />\r\n1) All the trek/tour will be conduct as private group basis<br />\r\n2) Minimum 2 pax to travel</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>All the transportation including airport transfer as per above itinerary.</li>\r\n	<li>All accommodation (Kathmandu) twin or triple sharing basis</li>\r\n	<li>All the meals as per above itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Complete 11 days lodge trek arrangement with:</li>\r\n	<li>Equipment: Sleeping bag with fleece inner liner</li>\r\n	<li>Manpower: English speaking Guide and porter</li>\r\n	<li>Miscellaneous: Permit for National park, trekking staff and porter insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Transportation: Kathmandu-Dhunche and Syabru Bensi &ndash; Kathmandu by 4x4 Jeep</li>\r\n	<li>All the entrance fees for place of visit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>International return air ticket with taxes</li>\r\n	<li>Visa fee (USD25)</li>\r\n	<li>Personal clothings</li>\r\n	<li>Client&#39;s travel Insurance coverage like rescue operation by any means of transportation</li>\r\n	<li>Alcoholic and other beverage,</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss</li>\r\n	<li>Theft and damage</li>\r\n	<li>Tips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '10', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 1200.00, 1150.00, 'Kathmandu', 'Kathmandu', 'package_banner_1469621559.jpg', NULL, 4, 1, 1, '1', '0', '1', '2016-07-27 13:31:57', '2016-08-08 16:37:40', NULL),
(58, 13, 1, '12 Days Annapurna Base Camp Trek ', '12-days-annapurna-base-camp-trek', '12 Days Annapurna Base Camp Trek ', '12 Days Annapurna Base Camp Trek ', '12 Days Annapurna Base Camp Trek ', '<p>The Annapurna Base Camp is a high glacial basin lying north of Pokhara. Many of the peaks are over 7000m, including the famous twin-peaked Machapuchare, as well as Annapurna I and lll, Annapurna South, Gangapurna and Glacier Dome. Enjoy mountain views, thick bamboo and rhododendron forests and a mix of cultures unparalleled by other treks as you venture deep into the Annapurna Himal.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Day 01: ARRIVE &ndash; KATHMANDU (D)</strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival, meet and transfer to hotel. Welcome drinks followed by briefing. Late afternoon leisure walk in <strong>Thamel</strong>, a popular tourist district in Kathmandu Valley (1300M) and a bustling bazaar which offers a glimpse of Nepal&rsquo;s vibrant ethnic culture. &ndash; O/N at Hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 02: KATHMANDU-POKHARA-BIRETHANTI (1000m) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast transfer to trek start point via Pokhara, drive will takes about&nbsp; 6 and half hrs. Lunch will be on the way. Upon arrival short walk for 30 mins to rest stop at Birethanti.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em><strong>Pokhara</strong></em><br />\r\nPokhara&rsquo;s pristine air, spectacular backdrop of snowy peaks, serene lakes and surrounding greenery make it &lsquo;the jewel in the Himalaya&rsquo;, a place of remarkable natural beauty. It is also the gateway to the Annapurna region where many trekkers finds his Shangri-la, The mesmerizing Annapurna massif towering over the valley includes peaks over 8000m such as Machhapuchhre (Mt. Fishtail), Annapurna 1 to IV, Annapurna South, Dhaulagiri and Manaslu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 03</strong>: <strong>BIRETHANTI-GHANDRUK</strong> <strong>(1890m)</strong> <strong>(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. From Birethanti, we trek uphill on the trail to Ghandruk. While on the trail, we again enjoy the panoramic views of the mountains, pass along various small villages like Chimrong, Syauli Bazar, and Chane. After crossing the suspension bridge over Khumnu Khola, we reach Ghandruk, a beautiful village mostly inhabited by the Gurung community. Along with enjoying the stunningly close-up towering views of Fishtail, Annapurna South, and Hiunchuli. We also acquaint ourselves with the simple but rich cultural traditions of the Gurung people at the Gurung Museum in Ghandruk.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 04: GHANDRUK-</strong><strong>CHHOMRUNG (2800m) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nTrek about 5 hours. The trail will be down hill and gradual flat, after lunch will be steep climb about 2 hrs all the way to Chhomrung. O/N at lodge. <strong>&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 05: CHHOMRUNG - DOVAN (about 2580m) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nWe head out of Chhomrong along the Modi Khola leaving behind inhabited foothills into the high step and wooded slopes of the Himalayas. We cross the suspension bridge then trek up to Sinuwa Danda. The ascent from Sinuwa becomes somewhat flatter. The trail passes through a thick and dark rhododendron forest up to Khuldighar. Then, we descend long and steep stone steps into deep bamboo and rhododendron forests through which we reach Dovan shortly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 06: DOVAN-DEURALI (about 3200m) (B,L,D)</strong> - Trek abt 5 hours. O/N at lodge.<br />\r\nThe day starts with a gentle gradual ascent following the trail above the river through thick bamboo, oak and rhododendron forests up the side of the canyon. We pass by Himalaya Hotel and cross two streams over small bridges. The trail passes through solitary places. We get a sense of peace from the beauty of Mother Nature that surrounds us.&nbsp; There is also the possibility of seeing a variety of wildlife species such as wild pigs, deer, and maybe even snow leopards. We climb again to Hinko Cave, an overhanging rock. Our further climb paves the way to Deurali.<strong> </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 07: DEURALI- MACHHAPUCHHARE BASE CAMP (3600m) (B,L,D) </strong><br />\r\nToday, we start our trek to Machhapuchhre Base Camp (MBC). We make a gentle climb through a river bed and then a steep climb over to the mountain side. There are avalanche prone areas at some point on the trail. We have to be on alert to protect ourselves. If there is any wind after about half an hour walk from Deurali, we will find ourselves in the middle of a river bed surrounded by giant snow-covered mountains. When the sun rises, the snow on the mountains shines and the river valley is filled with warm sun rays. The hike from Bagar to Machhapuchhre Base Camp is somewhat strenuous but the unfolding view of the majestic Machhapuchhre is certainly a rewarding experience. At this juncture, we enjoy the views of Mt. Hiunchuli, Annapurna South, Annapurna I, Annapurna III, Gangapurna and, of course, the Fishtail or Machhapuchhre itself.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 08: MACHHAPUCHHARE B. C &ndash; ANNAPURNA B.C &ndash; HIMALAYAN HOTEL (4095m) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nToday is highlight of whole trek. Early morning trek up to Annapurna Base Camp for 2 hrs. You can catch the <strong>beautiful sunrise over the Annapurna Range </strong>and spend some time to gaze at the <strong>South Annapurna Glacier</strong>. After that trek back to MBC for breakfast and down to Himalayan Hotel. About 6 hours trek. O/N at lodge. <strong>&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 09: HIMALAYAN HOTEL-CHHOMRUNG (B,L,D)</strong> - Trek about 6 hours. O/N at lodge. <strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 10: CHHOMRUNG-NAYAPUL-BIRETHANTI &ndash; POKHARA (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nToday the trek will be bit longer, about 3 hours down hill and another 4 hrs gradual walk. End of the trek at Birethanti and drive to <strong>Pokhara. </strong>Upon arrival check in hotel. Late afternoon some free time to explore the popular Lakeside Bazaar for some delightful bargains. Evening dinner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 11: POKHARA-KATHMANDU (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast &nbsp;drive to back to Kathmandu. Drive will takes about 5 hrs.&nbsp; Lunch will be on the way. Upon arrival check in Hotel. Late afternoon free to explore the colourful local market area and shopping. Evening enjoy a sumptuous <strong>traditional Nepalese Cuisine with Cultural Performance.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 12: KATHMANDU &ndash; FINAL DEPARTURE (B)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast&nbsp; check out and &nbsp;city tour &ndash; visit <strong>Kathmandu Durbar Square</strong>, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and if you are lucky, you will get a glimpse of the <strong>famous Kumari, the world&rsquo;s only living Goddess</strong>. This complex of palaces, courtyards and temples like Hanumandhoka Palace, Kumari Ghar (Abode of the Living Goddess), Taleju temple, built between the 12th and 18th centuries, used to be the seat of the ancient Malla Kings of Kathmandu.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the tour transfer to airport to for fly out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Land Package cost:&nbsp; SGD1190 Per pax (Based on 3 star standard hotel)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong><br />\r\n1) All the trek/tour will be conduct as private group basis<br />\r\n2) Minimum 2 pax to travel</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>All the transportation by private vehicle including airport transfer</li>\r\n	<li>3 nights accommodation in Kathmandu &amp; Pokhara</li>\r\n	<li>All the necessary ground transfers</li>\r\n	<li>Complete 09 days tea house trek arrangement</li>\r\n	<li>Equipment: Sleeping bag with fleece inner liner</li>\r\n	<li>Manpower: Trekking guide and a porter</li>\r\n	<li>Meals: All meals through out the trip as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Miscellaneous: National park fees, trekking guide and porters insurance</li>\r\n	<li>All the Entrance fees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>International return air ticket with all the taxes</li>\r\n	<li>Visa fee &ndash; apply upon arrival <strong>(USD25)</strong></li>\r\n	<li>Personal clothing</li>\r\n	<li>Travel Insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss</li>\r\n	<li>Theft and damage</li>\r\n	<li>Tips (Trekking guide, porter, city guide, driver)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '12', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 1210.00, 1190.00, 'Kathmandu', 'Kathmandu', 'package_banner_1469620576.jpg', NULL, 12, 1, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2016-07-27 13:59:35', '2016-08-08 16:37:28', NULL),
(59, 13, 1, '12 Days Nepal Ghandrung/Chhomrung Trek', '12-days-nepal-ghandrung-chhomrung-trek', '12 Days Nepal Ghandrung/Chhomrung Trek', '12 Days Nepal Ghandrung/Chhomrung Trek', '12 Days Nepal Ghandrung/Chhomrung Trek', '<p>Ghandrung trek is a short trek suitable for children as there are no long walking days and high altitudes plus there is always plenty to see. The trail passes through fascinating traditional Gurung villages at Dhampus &amp; Ghandrung; a nice opportunity to witness the culture and tradition of Nepalese countryside.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Day 01: Arrive &ndash; KATHMANDU (D)</strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival meet and transfer to hotel. Briefing and welcome drink. Late afternoon walking tour around <strong>Thamel</strong>, a popular tourist district in Kathmandu Valley and a bustling bazaar which offers a glimpse of Nepal&rsquo;s vibrant ethnic culture. Evening Dinner.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 02: KATHMANDU-POKHARA (900m) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nMorning meet in the hotel and transfer to bus station and take a bus to <strong>Pokhara. </strong>The Annapurna and the famous Machhapucchare (Commonly known as Fishtail ountain) tower over the tropical setting of Pokhara. Drive takes about 5 hours, lunch will be on the way. Upon arrival check-in to hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Late afternoon an hour leisure boating at scenic <strong>Lake Fewa</strong> and visit <strong>Barahi Temple </strong>in the middle of the lake. After that free time to enjoy walking around Lakeside and shopping. Evening dinner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 03: POKHARA- PHEDI- POTHANA (1800m)</strong> <strong>(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast drive to Phedi about 45 min and&nbsp; start trek.&nbsp; You will ascend stone-cut steps made by ancients of old to access villages from one to another.&nbsp; As you climb higher, the panoramic view of villages dots the land below till Dhampus. It will takes about 3 hrs. After Lunch continue trek to Pothana. It will take another 1 and half hours. Overnight at lodge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 04</strong>: <strong>POTHANA-LANDRUNG</strong> <strong>(1640m)</strong> <strong>(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek, today, the trail continues to ascend, albeit more gently, through fine forest of oak and rhododendron.&nbsp; Till Deurali (2555 m). After that trail will changed and about <strong>1 and half hours</strong> <strong>down till Tolkha village</strong>. You will have lunch at Tolkha. After lunch the trek will be gradual flat all the way to Landrung. Overnight at lodge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 05: LANDRUNG-GHANDRUNG (1960m)</strong> <strong>&nbsp;(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. Early part of the trek will be <strong>down hill about 1 hr</strong> after that cross the bridge and uphill all the way to Ghandrung, it will takes about 2 hrs. Upon reaching Ghandrung you will have lunch. Afternoon tour around the Ghandrung Village. You will able to see the <strong>Annapurna</strong><strong> range</strong> and <strong>Fishtail mountain range </strong>around you.&nbsp; Over night at lodge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 06: GHANDRUK-</strong><strong>CHHOMRUNG (2200m) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. Early part of the trek will be gradual flat all the way to till Kimrung danda about 2 hrs. After that some <strong>gradual</strong> &nbsp;<strong>down hill about 1 hr</strong> after that cross the bridge and some little uphill all the way to Chhomrung, it will takes about 2 hrs. Upon reaching Chhomrong check in Guest house. &nbsp;Chhomrung is the capital of the Annapurna Base Camp trek. You will able to see the good view of <strong>Annapurna range</strong> and <strong>Fishtail mountain range </strong>around you.&nbsp; Over night at lodge<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 07: CHHOMRUNG-NAYAPUL (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nMorning you will able to see the sunrise from your guest house. After breakfast start trek. Early part of the trek will be gradual down hill about 2 hr to Jhinudanda. This place offer the natural hot spring. After that cross the bridge, all the way mostly gradual flat till Nayapul. Total trek will be about 5 hrs. Overnight at guest house.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 08: NAYAPUL-BIRETHANTI-POKHARA (B,L,D)</strong> After breakfast start trek to Birethanti. The trail will be gradual flat with some down hill, it takes about 4 hours to reach Birethanti. You will have lunch at Birethanti. After lunch drive back to <strong>Pokhara, </strong>it will takes about 2 hrs. Upon arrival check-in hotel. Late afternoon walking around the lake side bazaar with some shopping.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 09: POKHARA &ndash; SARANGKOT &ndash; POKHARA (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nEarly morning, drive up to <strong>Sarangkot (</strong>1200m) sunrise view point for 30 minutes. Expect a very <strong>spectacular view of sunrise over the whole Annapurna range</strong> including the Machhapucchare of height close to 7000m. After sunrise, drive back to Pokhara for breakfast.<br />\r\nAfter that city tour to <strong>Tibetan Refugees&rsquo; Camp, Devi&rsquo;s Fall and Mahadev Gupteswar Cave. </strong>Evening enjoy walk around <strong>Lakeside Bazaar</strong> for some delightful shopping bargains followed by dinner.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 10: POKHARA &ndash; KATHMANDU &ndash; NAGARKOT (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast, drive to Nagarkot via Kathmandu. sunrise and sunset from this popular hill resort present you the <strong>breathtaking view of the Eastern Himalayan Range including Mt. Everest </strong>which can be seen on a clear day. It is a scenic drive with lots of lovely quaint little houses and paddy fields which takes about one and half hours. Drive takes about 6 hours. Lunch will be on the way. Upon arrival, check in Resort. Enjoy a relaxing short nature walk and catch the gorgeous sunset. Evening dinner.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><em>Option: You can take domestic flight- Pokhara to Kathmandu &ndash;it is only 25 min. (cost USD128)</em></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 11: NAGARKOT&ndash;KATHMANDU (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAwake in the morning to the cold but stunningly spectacular sunrise over Nagarkot Hill. The first ray of the sun firing the peak glimmering red, slowly lighting the Himalaya range. Mt Everest in the far east and Langtang and the Dhaulagiri peak in the west. After breakfast, drive back to Kathmandu. On the way, visit <strong>Kathmandu Durbar Square</strong>, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and if you are lucky, you will get a glimpse of the<strong> famous Kumari, the world&rsquo;s only living Goddess</strong>. This complex of palaces, courtyards and temples like Hanumandhoka Palace, Kumari Ghar (Abode of the Living Goddess), Taleju temple, built between the 12th and 18th centuries, used to be the seat of the ancient Malla Kings of Kathmandu. Lunch in the city centre.<br />\r\nAfter lunch visit <strong>Bouddhanath Stupa,</strong> one of the world&rsquo;s largest Stupa built in the fifth century AD. It looms 36 meters high and presents one of the most fascinating specimens of stupa design with hundreds of prayer wheels and 108 small images of Buddha all around. Late afternoon free to explore <strong>As an Toll</strong>, the colourful local market area and shopping. Evening enjoy a sumptuous traditional <strong>Nepalese Cuisine with Cultural Performance</strong>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 12: KATHMANDU &ndash; DEPARTURE (B)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast transfer to Airport for fly out according to your flight schedule.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Land Package cost: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SGD1200 Per pax (Based on 3 star standard hotel)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&bull; This is a private trip arrangements</li>\r\n	<li>&bull; Cost based on minimum 2 pax traveling</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>All the necessary transportation as per above itinerary.</li>\r\n	<li>All the accommodation as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>All the meals as per above itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Complete 6 days lodge trek arrangement with:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Equipment: Sleeping bag with fleece inner liner</li>\r\n	<li>Manpower: English Speaking guide and porter.</li>\r\n	<li>Miscellaneous: National park fees, trekking staff and porter insurance</li>\r\n	<li>One night Nagarkot resort package</li>\r\n	<li>City tour with English speaking tour guide</li>\r\n	<li>All the entrance fees for places of visit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>International air ticket with all the taxes</li>\r\n	<li>All the necessary arrangement in Kathmandu</li>\r\n	<li>Visa fee (USD25) &ndash; apply upon arrival</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li>All alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>Personal clothing</li>\r\n	<li>Laundry</li>\r\n	<li>Telephone bills</li>\r\n	<li>All personal expenses</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss, theft and damages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '12', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 1300.00, 1200.00, 'Kathmandu', 'Kathmandu', 'package_banner_1469615083.jpg', NULL, 15, 1, 1, '1', '1', '1', '2016-07-27 14:10:35', '2016-08-08 16:36:29', NULL),
(60, 13, 1, '14 Days Nepal Langtang & Gosainkunda Trek', '14-days-nepal-langtang-gosainkunda-trek', '14 Days Nepal Langtang & Gosainkunda Trek', '14 Days Nepal Langtang & Gosainkunda Trek', '14 Days Nepal Langtang & Gosainkunda Trek', '<p>Langtang is a narrow valley that lies just south of the Tibetan border. It is sandwiched between the main Himalayan range to the north and a slightly lower range of snowy peaks to the south. Langtang has over 70 glaciers of varying sizes. The three major areas are Langtang, Gosainkunda (a holy lake at 4300m) and Helambu. Gosainkunda is a sacred lake, which is very important for both Hindus and Buddhists. Helambu valley is very famous for its natural beauty and wonderful climate with the superb views of the magnificent snow-covered mountains. The area covers typical highland Sherpa villages along with beautiful Rhododendron forests.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Day 01: ARRIVE - KATHMANDU (D)</strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival, meet and transfer to hotel. Welcome drinks followed by briefing. Late afternoon leisure walk in <strong>Thamel,</strong> a popular tourist district in Kathmandu Valley (1300M) and a bustling bazaar which offers a glimpse of Nepal&rsquo;s vibrant ethnic culture. &ndash; Overnight at Hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 02: <strong>KATHMANDU-DHUNCHE (1960M) (B,L,D)</strong></strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast drive to Dhunche. It take about 6 hours.&nbsp; (about 190km) today the journey will be quite uncomfortable because of the road. You will drive along the Trisuli river&nbsp; then pass by Trisuli Bazaar&nbsp; till Trisuli Bazaar.&nbsp; Road condition&rsquo;s quite good but after that its about 90 km totally rough road all the way going up to Dhunche.&nbsp; Overnight at Dhunche.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 03: <strong>DHUNCHE-THULO SYABRU (2250m)</strong> (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. Total trek will be about 5 hours. The trial will be gradual uphill. Overnight at Lodge</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 04: THULO-<strong>SYABRU-LAMA HOTEL (2700M)</strong> (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. Total trek will be about 5 hours. Morning&nbsp; one and half hours down the a little bit up and straight along the river, then straight one hour&nbsp; and just before Lama hotel little bit up trek. Overnight at Lodge</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 05: LAMA HOTEL -LANGTANG (3307m)</strong> <strong>(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. Total trek will be about 6 hours. Morning little bit up about half hour then one hour straight then gradual climbing all the way up till Langtang. The day crossing some small villages will get some tea house and some jungle. Overnight at Lodge</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 06: LANGTANG -KYANJIN GOMPA</strong> (about 3870 m) <strong>(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. Total trek will be about 3 hours. Morning&nbsp; half an hour, little bit up then all the way straight till Kyangching, the day trek trail will be quite easy&nbsp; normally&nbsp; trekkers arrived in time for lunch and rest in the afternoon. Overnight at Lodge</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 07: KYANG CHING GOMPA (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nFull day execration around the Kyanjin Gompa. Visit Monastery, cheese factory. Kyanning Gompa is the last village for<br />\r\nLangtang region. Late afternoon some rest. Overnight at Lodge</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 08: KYANJIN GOMPA &ndash;LAMA HOTEL (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. Total trek will be about 7 hours. Overnight at Lodge</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 09: LAMA HOTEL- SHIN GOMPA (3320M) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. Total trek will be about 5 hours. The trial will be gradual uphill. Overnight at Lodge<strong> </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 10: SHIN GUMPA- GOSAINKUND (4460M) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. Total trek will be about 6 hours. The trial will be gradual uphill. Overnight at Lodge<strong> </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 11: GOSAINKUND- SHIN GOMPA (3430M) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek back to Shin Gompa. Total trek will be about 6 hours. Overnight at Lodge</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 12: </strong><strong>SHIN GOMPA-DHUNCHE</strong><strong> (846)&nbsp; </strong><strong>(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. Total trek will be about 5 hours. Overnight at Lodge</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 13: </strong><strong>DHUNCHE-</strong><strong> KATHMANDU (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nDrive will takes about 5 hours. Upon arrival check in hotel. Afternoon walking tour around Thamel with some shopping. Evening Dinner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 14: KATHMANDU- Home sweet home. (B)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast some time for last minute shopping and transfer to Airport for fly out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Land Package Cost:&nbsp;SGD1380 Per pax &nbsp;(</strong><strong>Based on 3 star standard hotel)</strong><strong> </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Note:<br />\r\n1) Cost based on minimum<br />\r\n2) pax travelling&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>All the transportation including airport transfer as per above itinerary.</li>\r\n	<li>All accommodation (Kathmandu) &nbsp;3 star standard hotel</li>\r\n	<li>All the meals as per above itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Complete 11 days lodge trek arrangement with:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Equipment: Sleeping bag with fleece inner liner</li>\r\n	<li>Manpower: English speaking Guide and one porter &nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Miscellaneous: Permit for National park, trekking staff and porter insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Transportation: Kathmandu-Dhunche &ndash; Kathmandu by private vehicle.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Return air ticket with all the taxes</li>\r\n	<li>Visa fee (USD25)</li>\r\n	<li>Personal clothings,</li>\r\n	<li>Client&rsquo;s travel Insurance coverage like rescue operation by any means of transportation,</li>\r\n	<li>Alcoholic and other beverages,</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss,</li>\r\n	<li>Theft and damage</li>\r\n	<li>Tips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '14', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 1400.00, 1380.00, 'Kathmandu', 'Kathmandu', 'package_banner_1470372663.jpg', NULL, 5, 1, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '2016-08-05 10:51:03', '2016-08-08 16:37:40', NULL),
(61, 13, 1, '15 Days Annapurna Base Camp Trek', '15-days-annapurna-base-camp-trek', '15 Days Annapurna Base Camp Trek', '15 Days Annapurna Base Camp Trek', '15 Days Annapurna Base Camp Trek', '<p>The Annapurna Base Camp is a high glacial basin lying north of Pokhara. Many of the peaks are over 7000m, including the famous twin-peaked Machapuchare, as well as Annapurna I and lll, Annapurna South, Gangapurna and Glacier Dome. Enjoy mountain views, thick bamboo and rhododendron forests and a mix of cultures unparalleled by other treks as you venture deep into the Annapurna Himal.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Day 01: ARRIVE &ndash; KATHMANDU</strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival, meet and transfer to hotel. Welcome drinks followed by briefing. Late afternoon leisure walk in <strong>Thamel</strong>, a popular tourist district in Kathmandu Valley (1300M) and a bustling bazaar which offers a glimpse of Nepal&rsquo;s vibrant ethnic culture. &ndash; O/N at Hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 02: KATHMANDU-POKHARA-BIRETHANTI (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast take drive to Birethanti via Pokhara, drive will takes about 6 hours. Begin short trek about 30 min to Birethanti.&nbsp; Overnight at lodge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 03: BIRETHANTI - ULLERI</strong> <strong>(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek.&nbsp; You will ascend stone-cut steps made by ancients of old to access villages from one to another.&nbsp; As you climb higher, the panoramic view of villages dots the land below.&nbsp; After Lunch will be steep climb up hill it will take about 2 and half hours. O/N at lodge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 04</strong>: <strong>ULLERI - GHOREPANI</strong> <strong>(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nToday, the trail continues to ascend, albeit more gently, through fine forest of oak and rhododendron.&nbsp; Ghorepani (2855 m) means &ldquo;horse-water&rdquo; in Nepalese.&nbsp; Indeed, along the whole trek, you probably have seen caravans of packed mules adorned beautifully thronging the high roads.&nbsp; Nestled on top of the mountain, this village is shrouded with clouds and offers the magnificient view of Dhaulagiri and Annapurna range. O/N at lodge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 05: GHOREPANI &ndash; POON HILL (3015 m)</strong> <strong>&nbsp;&ndash; TADAPANI (2630M) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nEarly morning climb to <strong>Poon Hill</strong> take about 1 hours 30 minute. This high point offers a panoramic 360 degrees Annapurna Range around you.&nbsp; Your climb will be well-timed such that you will be able to watch sunrise approaching the mountains.&nbsp; It will be a memorable experience to relish; especially catching the sight of the distant snow peaks bathed in a coat of gold. After spending morning at the Poon Hill then trek back to Ghorepani for breakfast. After breakfast trek to Tadapani trek about 5 hours. O/N at lodge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 06: TADAPANI-CHHOMRUNG (2800m) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nTrek about 5 hours. The trail will be down hill and gradual flat. O/N at lodge. <strong>&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 07: CHHOMRUNG - DOVAN (about 2300m) (B,L,D)</strong> - Trek abt 5 hours. O/N at lodge.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 08: DOVAN - MACHHAPUCHHARE BASE CAMP (3600m) (B,L,D) - </strong>Trek abt 6 hours. O/N at lodge. <strong>&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 09: MACHHAPUCHHARE B. C &ndash; ANNAPURNA B.C &ndash; HIMALAYAN HOTEL (4095m) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nToday is highlight of whole trek. Early morning trek up to Annapurna Base Camp for 2 hrs. You can catch the beautiful sunrise over the Annapurna Range<strong> </strong>and spend some time to gaze at the South Annapurna Glacier. After that trek back to MBC for breakfast and down to Himalayan Hotel. About 6 hours trek. O/N at lodge. <strong>&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 10: HIMALAYAN HOTEL-CHHOMRUNG (B,L,D)</strong> - Trek about 6 hours. O/N at lodge. <strong>&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 11: CHHOMRUNG- GHANDRUNG (B,L,D)</strong> - Trek about 5 hours. O/N at lodge. <strong>&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 12: GHANDRUNG-BIRETHANTI &ndash; POKHARA (B,L)</strong><br />\r\nTrek about 3 hours and drive to <strong>Pokhara</strong> check in hotel. Late afternoon some free time to explore the popular Lakeside Bazaar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 13: POKHARA (B)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast, city tour to Tibetan Refugees&rsquo; Camp, Devi&rsquo;s Fall and Mahadev Gupteswar Cave. Late afternoon free and easy enjoy walk around<strong> </strong>Lakeside Bazaar<strong> </strong>for some delightful shopping.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 14: POKHARA-KATHMANDU (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast drive to Kathmandu. &nbsp;Drive will takes about 5 hrs. Lunch will be on the way.<br />\r\nUpon arrival check in hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Late afternoon free to explore the colourful local market area and shopping. Evening enjoy a sumptuous<strong> </strong>traditional Nepalese Cuisine with Cultural Performance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 15: KATHMANDU &ndash; FINAL DEPARTURE (B)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast&nbsp; check out and city tour<br />\r\n<br />\r\nVisit Kathmandu Durbar Square, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and if you are lucky, you will get a glimpse of the famous Kumari, the world&rsquo;s only living Goddess. This complex of palaces, courtyards and temples like Hanumandhoka Palace, Kumari Ghar (Abode of the Living Goddess), Taleju temple, built between the 12th and 18th centuries, used to be the seat of the ancient Malla Kings of Kathmandu, after that transfer to Airport for fly out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Land package: &nbsp;SGD1450 per pax (Based on 3 star standard Hotel) </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Note:<br />\r\n1) Cost based on Minimum<br />\r\n2) pax to travel</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>All the transportation by private vehicle including airport transfer</li>\r\n	<li>4 nights accommodation on single room basis on 3 star standard hotel in Kathmandu &amp; Pokhara</li>\r\n	<li>All the necessary ground transfers</li>\r\n	<li>Complete 11 days tea house trek arrangement</li>\r\n	<li>Equipment: Sleeping bag with fleece inner liner</li>\r\n	<li>Manpower: Trekking guide and a porter</li>\r\n	<li>Meals: All meals through out the trip as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Miscellaneous: National park fees, trekking guide and porters insurance</li>\r\n	<li>All the Entrance fees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Return air ticket with all the taxes</li>\r\n	<li>Visa fee &ndash; apply upon arrival (USD25)</li>\r\n	<li>Personal clothing</li>\r\n	<li>Travel Insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss</li>\r\n	<li>Theft and damage</li>\r\n	<li>Tips (Trekking guide, porter, city guide, driver)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '15', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 1500.00, 1450.00, 'Kathmandu', 'Kathmandu', 'package_banner_1470372931.jpg', NULL, 16, 1, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '2016-08-05 10:55:31', '2016-08-08 16:36:29', NULL),
(62, 13, 1, '17 Days Nepal Everest Base Camp Trek', '17-days-nepal-everest-base-camp-trek', '17 Days Nepal Everest Base Camp Trek', '17 Days Nepal Everest Base Camp Trek', '17 Days Nepal Everest Base Camp Trek', '<p>The Annapurna Base Camp is a high glacial basin lying north of Pokhara. Many of the peaks are over 7000m, including the famous twin-peaked Machapuchare, as well as Annapurna I and lll, Annapurna South, Gangapurna and Glacier Dome. Enjoy mountain views, thick bamboo and rhododendron forests and a mix of cultures unparalleled by other treks as you venture deep into the Annapurna Himal.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Day 01: Kathmandu</strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival, meet and transfer to hotel. Check in &amp; trek briefing. Late afternoon leisure walk in Thamel, a popular tourist district in Kathmandu Valley and a bustling bazaar which offers a glimpse of Nepal&rsquo;s vibrant ethnic culture. (Hotel on your own)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 02: Kathmandu &ndash; Lukla (2800M)- Phakding 2600M (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter early breakfast, transfer to the domestic terminal of Kathmandu Airport for an early morning flight to Lukla a gateway destination from where our trek begins. After an adventurous 40 minute flight above the breathtaking green and white mountains, we reach the Tenzing-Hillary Airport at Lukla. This is one of the most beautiful air routes in the world culminating in a dramatic landing on a hillside surrounded by high mountains peaks. Upon arrival at Lukla, we meet our other crew members and after some packing and arrangements, we start our trek through the prosperous village of Lukla until we reach Phakding.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 03: Phakding &ndash; Namche Bazaar&nbsp; (B,L,D) 3440M</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. The trail will be gradual flat till Monjo (2.5 hrs). After lunch, continue trek to Jorsale (40 min) and after crossing bridge the trail will be uphill all the way to Namche Bazaar. This will be the bit difficult part as it is up hill (3 hrs).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 04: Namche Bazaar (Acclimatization Day) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nThis is the scheduled &lsquo;acclimatization&rsquo; day for this trek. It is advisable to stay active during the day instead idling. You have the option of relaxing and exploring Namche Bazaar itself with its internet cafes, shops, restaurants &amp; bakeries or take a short hike up to the famous airstrip at Syangboche</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 05: Namche &ndash; Tengboche&nbsp; (B,L,D) 3860M</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek. Trail will be gradual flat till Sanasa. This is the easiest trekking part for 3 hours. Along the way you will have many chances to see Mt Everest, Thamserku, Ama Dablama and Lotse. After Sanasa trail will be downhill till Phunki Thanga. Lunch at Phunki Thanga. After lunch continue trek to Tengboche for 3 hours.<em>Tengboche</em><br />\r\nTengboche is the highlight of this trek. Tengboche offer that best view of Mt Everest and many more mountains. Tengboche has a famous Tengboche Monastery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 06: Tengboche &ndash; Pheriche (B,L,D) 4400M</strong><br />\r\nWalking northeast through groves of juniper, rhododendron and fir, under a spectacular view of majestic Ama Dablam you arrive in Pangboche (3860m) for lunch and continue trek to Pheriche. Pheriche is home to numerous yak pastures and potato fields, is located in a wide, windswept part of the valley.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 07: Pheriche&nbsp;(Acclimatization Day) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nFull day rest for acclimatization.<em>Himalayan Rescue Association</em><br />\r\nThe Himalayan Rescue Association (HRA) runs a clinic/health post in Pheriche for trekkers and porters during peak trekking months. Talks on how to avoid altitude sickness are given daily.&nbsp; The HRA clinic can provide emergency communications (not as a public service) through their daily radio contact with Kathmandu and a satellite phone.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 08: Pheriche &ndash; Lobuche&nbsp; (B,L,D) 4920M</strong><br />\r\nLeaving Pheriche the trail heads up the drainage of the Khumbu across a fairly level wind swept outwash plain. After about an hour it starts to climb steeply up the terminal moraine of the Khumbu Glacier. The trail now continues on fairly level on the west side of the lateral moraine before reaching Lobuche.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 09: Lobuche &ndash; Gorak Shep (B,L,D) 5100M</strong><br />\r\nWe start early from Lobuche and trek along the western side of the broad Khumbu Valley, through meadows and over scree slopes, as we continue beside the moraine of the huge creaking glacier. The trail is rough in parts and it is important to progress slowly as we are now above 5000m for the first time. Shortly the pyramid peak of Pumori (7145m) comes into view and underneath this, dwarfed by its more exotic neighbour, we see the small black peak of Kala Pattar (5545m). This is the best vantage point for views of Everest and is our objective for tomorrow. The trail then descends off the moraine and down to the small settlement of Gorak Shep (5160m) where we rest.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 10: Gorak Shep &ndash; Kala Patthar &ndash;&nbsp;Gorak Shep (B,L,D) </strong><br />\r\nThe ascent takes approx. 2 hours of steady walking to Kala Pather, stopping occasionally to take in the view of the increasing bulk of Everest. From the summit it is possible to see many of the key features of this great mountain &ndash; the South Col from which Hillary and Tenzing made their first ascent in 1953 is clearly visible. After spending time taking photographs and experiencing the greatest mountain view in the world we descend back to Gorak Shep for breakfast. After breakfast continue trek down to Lobuche.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 11: Gorak Shep &ndash; Everest Base Camp &ndash;&nbsp;Pheruche (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nEarly morning after breakfast set off to Everest Base Camp it will takes about 2 hrs to reach. Upon reaching spend some time taking picture after that return back to Gorak Shep and then continue down to Pheruche. Today you will be walking about 5to 7 hrs. We can now look forward to a reduction in altitude and easier going, as we descend back down the trail that we trekked up only a few days ago.<br />\r\n<em>Note: This is subject to every trekkers walking condition, may change to stay at Labuche if not able to reach Pheruche. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 12: </strong><strong>Pheruche-Tengboche-Namache (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nEarly morning breakfast and&nbsp; set off for Namche. It will very long day- about 7 to 8 hours of trek. Although can now look forward to a reduction in altitude and easier going, as we descend back down the trail that we trekked up only a few days ago. There is sometimes a sense of anti-climax about the return trek, however it is a chance to relax now that the hard part is over, and concentrate on those aspects of mountain life that may have been overlooked on the way up. The walking now seems easier due to the fact that our bodies are acclimatized.<br />\r\n<em>Note: This is subject to every trekkers walking condition, may change to stay at Phunki thanga if not able to reach Namche.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 13: Namche &ndash;Jorsale-Lukha (B,L,D) 2850M</strong><br />\r\nEarly morning breakfast and&nbsp; set off for Lukla. It will very long day- about 7 hours of trek. The final day of our trek, we retrace our steps along the trail above the Dudh Kosi before turning off the main Jiri route and rising up to Lukla.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 14: Lukla (Trek Buffer Day)</strong> <strong>(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast full day &nbsp;rest and relax. Option, if you get the flight, try to fly back to Kathmandu as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 15: Lukla-Kathmandu</strong> <strong>(B)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast connect short flight to Kathmandu. Upon arrival pick up and transfer to hotel. (Hotel own arrangement)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 16: Kathmandu (Buffer Day)</strong> <strong>(B) </strong>(Hotel own arrangement)<br />\r\nAfter breakfast city tour visit Kathmandu Durbar Square, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and if you are lucky, you will get a glimpse of the famous Kumari, the world&rsquo;s only living Goddess. After lunch, visit Bouddhanath Stupa,one of the world&rsquo;s largest Stupa built in the fifth century AD. Late afternoon explore Asan Tol, the colourful local market area and shopping.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>An Important Note:</em><br />\r\nAll our itineraries for the Everest region include one buffer day at the end of the trip. This is because often the Kathmandu-Lukla-Kathmandu flight gets delayed by a few hours or may even be cancelled for one, two, or more days due to unfavourable weather conditions even in the best seasons. We will try our best to arrange the next flight for you. We also organize Helicopter rescue in such conditions, if it is available and upon request by clients. In event of flight delay, the program for this day will be as adjusted accordingly from the time you arrive Kathmandu.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em>In case the flight delay/cancellation happens at the start of trip and it goes so long that it disturbs your onward travel schedule, we will provide you an alternative trek in other region.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 17: Kathmandu- Final Departure (B)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast check out of hotel transfer to airport for departure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Land Package with Domestic flight: SGD2280 Per pax&nbsp; (Based on 3 star standard hotel) </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Note:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1) Minimum 2 pax to travel&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Private A/C transportation including airport transfer</li>\r\n	<li>Return domestic airfare with taxes (Kathmandu &ndash; Lukla &ndash; Kathmandu)</li>\r\n	<li>Personal English speaking tour guide</li>\r\n	<li>Meals as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Entrance fees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Trek:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1 Head trekking guide throughout the trip</li>\r\n	<li>Required Porter (1 porter to every 2 trekkers, each trekker bag up to 15 kg)</li>\r\n	<li>Insurance for trekking crew</li>\r\n	<li>Lodge/Guest house accommodation</li>\r\n	<li>Sleeping bag with fleece inner liner</li>\r\n	<li>Trek permit and national park fees</li>\r\n	<li>1 Trekking Map per trekker (provided in Nepal)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Return International air ticket</li>\r\n	<li>Hotel in Kathmandu</li>\r\n	<li>Nepal visa (apply upon arrival USD30)</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>Personal &amp; trek expenses (including hot shower, drinking water, battery charging)</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss, theft and damages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '17', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 5545, NULL, 'Oct–Dec & Mar–May', NULL, 2300.00, 2280.00, 'Kathmandu', 'Kathmandu', 'package_banner_1470373420.jpg', NULL, 17, 1, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '2016-08-05 11:03:40', '2016-08-08 16:36:29', NULL);
