(63, 13, 1, '17 Days Nepal Annapurna Circuit ', '17-days-nepal-annapurna-circuit', '17 Days Nepal Annapurna Circuit ', '17 Days Nepal Annapurna Circuit ', '17 Days Nepal Annapurna Circuit ', '<p>This circuit of Annapurna &ndash; rightly known as Nepal&rsquo;s classic trek &ndash; offers more variety than any other walks of equivalent length and takes you through virtually every type of scenery that Nepal has to offer. There are superb views of Annapurna and Dhaulagiri, and the constant variety of landscapes ranges from sub-tropical through alpine to an arid semi-desert similar to Tibet; at the climax of the trek there&rsquo;s a formidable 5416m pass, the Thorong La, to cross.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Day 01: ARRIVE &ndash; KATHMANDU</strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival, meet and transfer to hotel. Welcome drinks followed by briefing. Late afternoon leisure walk in Thamel, a popular tourist district in Kathmandu Valley (1300M) and a bustling bazaar which offers a glimpse of Nepal&rsquo;s vibrant ethnic culture. &ndash; Overnight at Hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 02:&nbsp; KATHMANDU-BESISHAR-BHULBHULE </strong><strong>(790m)</strong><strong> </strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast drive to Besishar. It will takes about 4 hours and change the local transport to Khudi will takes another 1 and half hours. Upon reaching Khudi&nbsp; and short trek to Bhulbhule&nbsp; and check in lodge. Overnight at lodge. (B,L,D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 03:&nbsp; BHULBHULE-BAHUNDANDA </strong><strong>(1310m)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek &ndash; total trek will be about 5 hours. Overnight at lodge (B,L,D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 04:&nbsp; BHUNDANDA-CHAMJE</strong><strong>(1430m)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek &ndash; total trek will be about 6 hours. Overnight at lodge (B,L,D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 05:&nbsp;CHAMJE-DHARAPANI (1860)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek &ndash; total trek will be about 5 hours. Overnight at lodge (B,L,D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 06:&nbsp; DHARAPANI-KOTO </strong><strong>(2600m)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek &ndash; total trek will be about 5 hours. Overnight at lodge (B,L,D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 07:&nbsp; KOTHO-PISANG </strong><strong>(abt 3200m)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek &ndash; total trek will be about 5 hours. Overnight at lodge (B,L,D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 08: PISANG-MANANG </strong><strong>(3540m)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek &ndash; total trek will be about 5 hours. Overnight at lodge (B,L,D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 09: MANANG</strong>&ndash; Full day rest for the acclimatization. Overnight at lodge (B,L,D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 10: MANANG- YAK KHARKA</strong><strong>(abt 3800m)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek &ndash; total trek will be about 4 hours and rest for more acclimatization.<br />\r\nOvernight at lodge (B,L,D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 11: YAK KHARKA-LETDAR</strong><strong>(abt 4200m)</strong><strong> </strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek &ndash; total trek will be about 3 and half hours and rest for more acclimatization.<br />\r\nOvernight at lodge (B,L,D) <strong> </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 12: LETHDAR-THORUNG PHEDI </strong><strong>(4441m)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek &ndash; total trek will be about 4 hours. Afternoon more time for rest.Overnight at lodge (B,L,D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 13:&nbsp; THORUNG PHEDI TO THORONG PASS &amp; CROSS THE PASS</strong> and trek down to MUKTINATH (3760m)<br />\r\nThis day early morning start to climb up to the Thorong pass (5416 m). From the Top of the Pass you will able to see 360 degree Western Himalayan Range. Then trek down to Muktinath. Total trek will be about 8 hrs. Overnight at lodge (B,L,D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 14: MUKTINATH-JOMSOM </strong><strong>(2800m)</strong> After breakfast start trek &ndash; total trek will be about 4 hours. Overnight at lodge (B,L,D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 15: JOMSOM-POKHARA </strong><strong>(B)</strong><strong> </strong><br />\r\nEarly morning short walk to airport and connect 20min flight to Pokhara. Pokhara (900m) another popular tourist destination.The Annapurna Mountain Range and the famous Machhapucchare (Commonly known as Fishtail Mountain) tower over the tropical setting of Pokhara. The Dhaulagiri and Manaslu ranges, each with peaks over 8000 m, can be seen from Pokhara. You will have great view of the ranges from the flight. Upon arrival transfer to hotel, check-in hotel and breakfast.&nbsp; Free and easy with rest and afternoon some free time for shopping along the Lakeside Bazaar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 16: POKHARA-KATHMANDU (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfastdrive &nbsp;to &nbsp;Kathmandu. &nbsp;Drive will takes about 5 hrs. Lunch will be on the way. Upon arrival check in hotel.Late afternoon free to explore Thamel colourful local market area and shopping.Evening enjoy a sumptuous traditional Nepalese Cuisine with Cultural Performance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 17: KATHMANDU- Home sweet home. (B)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast some time for last minute shopping and transfer to Airport for fly out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Land package: SGD1750 per pax (Based on 3 star standard hotel )</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong><br />\r\n1) Minimum 2 pax to travel</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Domestic airfare (Jomsom-Pokhara) including all the taxes</li>\r\n	<li>All the transportation by private vehicle including airport transfer</li>\r\n	<li>Complete 13Nights lodge trek arrangement with</li>\r\n	<li>Equipment:&nbsp; Sleeping bag with fleece inner liner</li>\r\n	<li>Manpower: Trekking guide</li>\r\n	<li>All meals as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Miscellaneous: National park fees, trekking guide insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Transportation as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>3 Nights accommodation on twin sharing basis in Kathmandu &amp; Pokhara</li>\r\n	<li>All the necessary ground transfers</li>\r\n	<li>All the entrance fees for sightseeing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Domestic airfare (Jomsom-Pokhara) including all the taxes</li>\r\n	<li>All the transportation by private vehicle including airport transfer</li>\r\n	<li>Complete 13Nights lodge trek arrangement with</li>\r\n	<li>Equipment:&nbsp; Sleeping bag with fleece inner liner</li>\r\n	<li>Manpower: Trekking guide</li>\r\n	<li>All meals as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Miscellaneous: National park fees, trekking guide insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Transportation as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>3 Nights accommodation on twin sharing basis in Kathmandu &amp; Pokhara</li>\r\n	<li>All the necessary ground transfers</li>\r\n	<li>All the entrance fees for sightseeing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '17', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 5500, NULL, '', NULL, 1800.00, 1750.00, 'Kathmandu', 'Kathmandu', 'package_banner_1470373696.jpg', NULL, 18, 1, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '2016-08-05 11:08:16', '2016-08-08 16:36:29', NULL),
(64, 13, 1, '18 Days Gokyo, Chola Pass- Kalapather& Everest Base Camp Trek', '18-days-gokyo-chola-pass-kalapather-everest-base-camp-trek', '18 Days Gokyo, Chola Pass- Kalapather& Everest Base Camp Trek', '18 Days Gokyo, Chola Pass- Kalapather& Everest Base Camp Trek', '18 Days Gokyo, Chola Pass- Kalapather& Everest Base Camp Trek', '<p>This trek gives you the grand tour of the famous Khumbu area. This is a strenuous trek leading to Gokyo Lake and over the Cho La Pass leading into the Khumbu valley above Lobuche. The trail continues up to Kalapattar and then back to Lukla via Thengboche and Namche Bazaar.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Day 01: Arrive &ndash;Katmandu </strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival meet and transfer to hotel. Welcome drinks followed by briefing. Late afternoon leisure walk in Thamel, a popular tourist district in Kathmandu Valley and a bustling bazaar which offers a glimpse of Nepal&rsquo;s vibrant ethnic culture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 02: Kathmandu (B)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast half day city tour visit Patan Durbar Square which is one of the three major cities in Kathmandu Valley, famous for its Buddhist monuments and Hindu Temples. Watch the traditional artisans working with wood, stones and metals and afternoon free and easy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 03: Kathmandu- Lukla (2800 m)-Phakding</strong>(B,L,D)<br />\r\nAfter breakfast dive to airport and take short flight to Lukla then trek to Phakding&nbsp; (2600 m) takes about 4 hours. Overnight at Lodge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 04: Phakding - Namche Bazar (3440 m)</strong>(B,L,D)<br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek &ndash; total trek will be about 5 hours. Overnight at Lodge</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 05: Namche Bazaar</strong>(B,L,D)<br />\r\nRest day for acclimatization &ndash; visit Shyangbuche for 1 hr hike. From this point you can have good view of AmaDablam, Nuptse, Lhotse and Everest. There are also good views from the National Park Centre and Museum just above the village and come back to Namcne Bazaar. After lunch rest and relax.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 06: Namche Bazar &ndash;PhortseTenga (3680)</strong>(B,L,D)<strong> </strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast trek to PhortseTenga. Total trek will be about 5 hrs.<strong> </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 07: PhortseTenga-Machhermo (4470 m)</strong>(B,L,D)<br />\r\nTrek about 6 hours. Over night at Lodge</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 08: Machhermo-Gokya (4790m)</strong>(B,L,D)<br />\r\nTrek about 5 hours. Over night at Lodge</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 09: Gokyo-Gokyo- Ri &ndash;Thagna</strong>(B,L,D)<br />\r\nEarly morning climb to GokhyaRi 5483m to see the good sunrise view, it will takes about 2 hrs up. You will see the sunrise view over the eastern Himalayan Ranges. Spend some time taking good pictures. After that trek down to Gokyo. You will have breakfast after breakfast&nbsp; trek to Thagna. Trek about 4 hrs. Over night at simple lodge.<br />\r\nNote: This place have only basic lodge in operation- sometime may be close, if is close you will have very basic food for that night- like noodles soup.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 10: Thangna-Cross Chola pass (5420m) and trek to Dzonglha</strong>(B,L,D)<br />\r\nToday start early morning to climb up to CholaPass, the trail will be steep up almost all the way to the top of the Chola Pass (5420m). It will takes about 4 hrs to reach the top, once you reach the top you will have some time to take photo and enjoy the great view of Everest Ranges. After that trek down to Dhonglha, this will takes another about 3 hrs. Once you reach check in to the simple guest house and rest overnight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 11:</strong>Dzonglha-Labuche(B,L,D)<br />\r\nTrek about 4 hrs. Over night at Lodge</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 12: Lobuche - GorakShep (5100 m)</strong>(B,L,D)<br />\r\nTrek 3 hrs, upon reaching have lunch.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Note: After lunch if all of you are fine go to short excursion to Everest Base Camp and back to GorakShep. It will takes about 2 hrs. At that time Everest base camp will be crowded as you can see lots of Mt Everest Expedition teams base camp set up. After visiting Base camp trek back to GorakShep. Overnight at Lodge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 13: GorakShep - Kala Pattar (5545 m) &ndash; Labuche</strong>.&nbsp; (B,L,D)<br />\r\nEarly morning trek up to Kala Patthar to catch the world best sunrise with magnificent view of Mount Everest and may more, back to GorakShep, after breakfast trek to Everest Base camp if you did not go on the day 13. After that trek back to Labuche,&nbsp; Overnight at Lodge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 14: Labuche- Deboche</strong> &ndash; Trek about 6 hrs. Evening dinner together.Overnight at lodge. (B,L,D)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 15: Deboche &ndash;Jorsalle</strong>&ndash; Trek about 6 hours. Over night at Lodge&nbsp; (B,L,D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 16: Jorsalle-Lukla</strong> &ndash; Trek about 5 hrs. Overnight at lodge (B,L,D)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 17: Lukla &ndash;Kathmandu</strong>(B) - Upon arrival meet and transfer to hotel. Rest and relax.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 18: Kathmandu (B,D)</strong><strong> </strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast city tour &ndash; visit Kathmandu Durbar Square, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and if you are lucky, you will get a glimpse of the famous Kumari, the world&rsquo;s only living Goddess. This complex of palaces, courtyards and temples like Hanumandhoka Palace, Kumari Ghar (Abode of the Living Goddess), Taleju temple, built between the 12th and 18th centuries, used to be the seat of the ancient Malla Kings of Kathmandu. Lunch in the city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After lunch visit Bouddhanath Stupa, one of the world&rsquo;s largest Stupa built in the fifth century AD. It looms 36 meters high and presents one of the most fascinating specimens of Stupa design with hundreds of prayer wheels and 108 small images of Buddha all around. All the Buddhist throng to this Stupa to take part in the sacred rituals during the Buddhist festivals. Transfer back to hotel. Late afternoon free to explore market area and shopping. Evening enjoy a sumptuous traditional Nepalese Cuisine with Cultural Performance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 19: Kathmandu &ndash; final Depart&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast transfer to airport. (B)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Land package: </strong>SGD2380Per pax(Based on 3 start standard hotel)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong><br />\r\n1) Minimum 2 pax to travel</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Domestic air ticket &ndash;Kathmandu-Lukla-Kathmandu with all the taxes</li>\r\n	<li>All the transportation including airport transfers as per above itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Complete 14 Days lodge&nbsp; trek arrangement&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Equipment: Sleeping bag with fleece inner liner</li>\r\n	<li>Manpower: Trekking guide, Porters</li>\r\n	<li>Meals: All meals as per above itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Miscellaneous: National park fees, trekking guide and porters insurance</li>\r\n	<li>All the necessary ground transfers</li>\r\n	<li>3 nights accommodation (3 star standard hotel)&nbsp; in Kathmandu twin or triple sharing basis</li>\r\n	<li>Chola- Pass cross equipment, like Rope and Ice-X</li>\r\n	<li>All the entrance fees for places of visit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>International air ticket with all the taxes</li>\r\n	<li>Visa fee (USD40)</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li>All alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>Personal clothing</li>\r\n	<li>Laundry</li>\r\n	<li>Telephone bills</li>\r\n	<li>All personal expenses</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss, theft and damages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '18', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 2400.00, 2380.00, 'Kathmandu', 'Kathmandu', 'package_banner_1470373892.jpg', NULL, 19, 1, NULL, '0', '1', '1', '2016-08-05 11:11:32', '2016-08-08 16:36:29', NULL),
