(69, 15, 7, '09 Days India Golden Triangle Tour with Kashmir', '09-days-india-golden-triangle-tour-with-kashmir', '09 Days India Golden Triangle Tour with Kashmir', '09 Days India Golden Triangle Tour with Kashmir', '09 Days India Golden Triangle Tour with Kashmir', '<p>09 Days India Golden Triangle Tour with Kashmir</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Day 01:&nbsp;&nbsp; Arrive &ndash; Delhi&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\nDepart evening flight from Singapore, arrive Delhi late night. Meet and transfer to hotel. Overnight in Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 02:&nbsp; Delhi (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast, tour of Delhi visiting <strong>Raj Ghat</strong> and <strong>Shanti Vana</strong> &ndash; the cremation sites of Mahatma Gandhi and Jawaharlal Nehru, Jama Masjid. Later, take time to explore the famous <strong>Red Fort</strong>, a 17th century fort complex constructed by the Mughal emperor Shah Jahan in the walled city of Old Delhi. After lunch we continue our journey to visit <strong>Qutub Minar</strong> built by Qutub-ud-Din Aibek in 1199, <strong>Humayun&rsquo;s Tomb</strong> and <strong>India Gate</strong> (War Memorial Arch). Evening leisure walk around <strong>Connaught Place</strong>. The colonial buildings which have withstood the tyranny of times stand in magnificent glory, while shopping bazzars, restaurants, banks and airline offices attract millions everyday. There are some excellent bookshops you can check out for materials on India here. Overnight in Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 03: Delhi &ndash; Agra (256 km &ndash; 5/6 hrs) &nbsp;(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nDrive to Agra. Enroute we visit <strong>Fatehpur Sikri</strong> . Fatehpur Sikri is 40 km from Agra and built by Emperor Akbar in 1569 and abandoned after 15 years due to scarcity of water. The complex of buildings, including the extant royal palaces, courts and the <strong>Jama Masjid</strong> is a popular tourist attraction, and was declared a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 1986. Evening take a leisure stroll in the streets of Agra and soak in the local atmosphere. Overnight in Agra.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 04: &nbsp;Agra (Taj Mahal) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nEarly morning visit the world famous <strong>Taj Mahal, </strong>the epitome of Mughal art, built by the Moghul Emperor Shahjehan in 1630 for his Queen Mumtaz Mahal to enshrine her mortal remains. The <strong>Yamuna</strong><strong> River</strong> which flows behind the Taj Mahal, is a huge draw for photographers who wish to capture the sunrise and sunset view of the Taj reflected on Yamuna. When at the Taj, take a photo at &lsquo;Lady Di&rsquo;s Chair&rsquo; as a momento. Princess Diana sat on that chair to enjoy Taj Mahal during her visit in 1992 &ndash; it&rsquo;s the best position to see the beauty of Taj Mahal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Later visit the <strong>Agra Fort</strong> containing the Pearl Mosque, the Halls of Public and Private Audience. A UNESCO World Heritage site, it is the most important fort in India. The great Mugals, lived here, and the country was governed from here. It contained the largest state treasury and was visited by foreign ambassadors, travelers and dignitaries. Also visit the <strong>Tomb of Itmad-ud-Daullah</strong> built by Empress Noorjehan in memory of her father. Overnight in Agra.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 05:&nbsp; Agra &ndash; Delhi (203 km &ndash; 4 hrs) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nMorning free at leisure in Agra. Afternoon drive to Delhi. Upon reaching check in hotel. Overnight at Dehlhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 06:&nbsp; Delhi-Srinagar (1850m) &nbsp;(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast transfer to&nbsp;domestic&nbsp;airport to take a short (60m) flight to Srinagar.&nbsp;Upon arrival Srinagar&nbsp; you will be received and transfer to houseboat in Dal Lake.&nbsp;After lunch visit to Moghul Gardens. After that back to Dal Lake. Walking tour around the market and evening transfer to boat house. Dinner in the Boathouse .Over night in the houseboat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 07: Srinagar &ndash; Gulmarg ( (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nEarly morning you will see the Sunrise view over the Dal Lake.&nbsp; After that you will enjoy the boat house breakfast.&nbsp; After that check out and drive to Gulmarg. You will drive by normal car till Tangmarg, drive will takes about 1 hour. You stop for short break at Tangmarg&nbsp; and&nbsp;change the special 4W drive by Jeep to Gulmarg. It will takes about 45 min. You will drive through the Snow path route. Upon reaching Gulmarg check in Resort.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The name &#39;Gulmarg&#39; means &#39;meadow of flowers&#39; and without a doubt the town is an out of the world beauty, the entire area will be covered with thick layers of snow. Gulmarg offered world class skiing facilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will have lunch.&nbsp;After lunch meet up with your Ski Instructor&nbsp; and &nbsp;visit the Ski Shop&nbsp;to take the necessary Ski equipment. After that you will go for basic Ski lesson in house. After that your&nbsp; instructor will take you for Ski experience cover - Slopes and Lifts for about 2 hrs. Evening back to resort and dinner. Overnight at Resort.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 08:&nbsp; Gulmarg -Srinagar &nbsp;(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast check out and&nbsp; return to Srinagar.&nbsp;Upon arrival transfer to houseboat. Have lunch in the boat house.&nbsp; Afternoon visit the Srinager city for some shopping. Late afternoon enjoy the 1 hr Shikara (Boat) ride at Dal Lake. Overnight at Boat house. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 09:&nbsp; Srinagar &ndash; Delhi &ndash;&nbsp; Final Departure &nbsp;(B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast, transfer to airport for your flight to Delhi. Upon arrival, meet and start tour around Delhi. Visit <strong>Indian Gate</strong>, <strong>President Palace</strong> and <strong>Red Ford.</strong> You will have lunch in the city center. Late after noon free time for shopping. You will have dinner. After dinner transfer to airport and connect flight back to Singapore.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Minimum 2 pax to travel</li>\r\n	<li>Taj Mahal closed on Friday</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Domestic air fare with all the taxes</li>\r\n	<li>All private transportation including airport transfers as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>English speaking tour guide and tour escort as per itinerary throughout the trip</li>\r\n	<li>Accommodation twin or triple sharing basis</li>\r\n	<li>All the meals as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>All the entrances fees for places of visit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>International air ticket</li>\r\n	<li>India visa</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li>All alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>Personal clothing</li>\r\n	<li>Laundry</li>\r\n	<li>Telephone bills</li>\r\n	<li>All personal expenses</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss, theft and damages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '9', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 0.00, 2000.00, 'Singapore', 'Singapore', NULL, NULL, 6, 1, 1, '0', '0', '1', '2016-08-07 13:02:25', '2016-08-09 17:05:17', NULL),
