it</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Return international air ticket with all the taxes</li>\r\n	<li>India Visa &ndash; Apply in Singapore.</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li>All alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>All personal expenses</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss, theft and damages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '9', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 0.00, 2100.00, '', '', NULL, NULL, 8, 1, 1, '0', '0', '1', '2016-08-08 10:50:17', '2016-08-08 16:37:40', NULL),
(75, 17, 1, '11 Days Ladakh Adventure Markha Valley Trek ', '11-days-ladakh-adventure-markha-valley-trek', '11 Days Ladakh Adventure Markha Valley Trek ', '11 Days Ladakh Adventure Markha Valley Trek ', '11 Days Ladakh Adventure Markha Valley Trek ', '<p>Leh - Ladakh is the largest province within the North Indian State of Jammu and Kashmir, covering approximately 60,000 square miles (100,000 sq. km). It is surrounded and bisected by some of the highest mountain ranges in the world. Running in a generally northwest to southeast direction through Ladakh, the great Himalayan Range separates the Vale of Kashmir from Ladakh. We have various Tour Packages for your ready reference, though we believe on Tailor Made Itineraries for your scheduled trip to Ladakh and kashmir.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Very little is known for certain about Ladakh prior to the 7th century. In the 7th and 8th centuries Tibetanisation of Ladakh began. Still existent chronicles refer to the area of Ladakh as part of Tibet. Ladakh was also influenced by Kashmir, at the time a Buddhist region. Kashmiri artistic influence can still be seen in the wood carvings of the early monasteries at Lamayuru and Alchi, and early Kashmiri Buddhist bronze statues are found in several Ladakh monasteries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The Markha Valley trek lies in Ladakh &ndash; The land of passes. The Markha Valley trek is certainly one of the most diverse trek in the Western Himalayas and the barren landscape of Leh Ladakh and its unique Buddhist culture makes it even more special. It ventures into the two high Himalayas Mountain Passes over 15000 feet. Markha Valley trek trails wind past willow groves, alongside patches of wild roses and through canyons decorated with multi coloured Tibetan prayer flags rising and falling in the breeze. The Markha Valley Trek goes inside Hemis National park and gives an opportunity to meet the nomadic families as they herd their yaks.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The ubiquitous &ldquo;Chortens&rdquo; &ndash; Stupas, Tibetan multi coloured prayer flags and Monasteries signify the regions immersion in Buddhism. During the Markha valley trek one can connect with Tibet and immerse oneself in Tibetan culture.</strong></p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Day 01: Arrive &ndash; Delhi</strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival meet and transfer to hotel in Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 02</strong>: <strong>Delhi &ndash;Leh (3524m) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nEarly morning pick up and drop to airport to connect flight to Leh. This is 1 hr and 20 min scenic flight to Leh, during your Flight you will able to see the Great Ladakh mountain view throughout the flight. Upon arrival in Leh airport meet and greets By our local representative. After that transfer to hotel drive will takes about 20 min.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon arrival welcome drinks check in and rest till lunch time. This is to acclimatization.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will have lunch in the hotel. After lunch your guide will bring you around&nbsp; to explore the main market of Leh, where local&nbsp;Ladakhi women sale vegetable with little basket in traditional dress. After the short tour back to hotel for Dinner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 03</strong>: <strong>Leh (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast visit <strong>start day tour around Ladakh visit old palaces of Leh</strong> and visit famous <strong>Leh Army Museum</strong>. After lunch free at leisure around Leh. Overnight in Leh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Late after noon visit <strong>Shanti Stupa</strong> for <strong>Sunset Tour</strong>. The stupa is located on the hill top of the Changspa locality in Leh, it was built in 1983 on the rock and&nbsp; inaugurated by HH Dalai Lam. From this stupa you can see the memorable sunset over the Leh Valley. After that back to Leh and some free time for shopping. Evening dinner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 04</strong><strong>:&nbsp;Leh &ndash; Zinchen &ndash; Rumbak ( 3 &ndash; &nbsp;4 hrs Walk ) 3800 mts. (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast we drive to Zinchen where we start our trek. Enroute we visit Spitok monastery. Our ponies &amp; trekking crew will be waiting for us at Zinchen.&nbsp;The trail is straightforward as we follow the Jinchen Nala upstream. The valley closes in around us while amazing rock formations tower above us. We may have to cross the river as the stream forces the path closer to the side of the valley. Suddenly the valley widens and reveals the snow-topped peaks of the Stok mountains. Prayer flags on a wide pasture mark the junction with the trail leading to Rumbak. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 05:&nbsp;</strong><strong> Rumbak &ndash; Base of Gandala (4450 mts) 4 &ndash; 5 hrs walk. (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek, looking left towards Rumbak a fantastic multi-coloured peaked skyline ridge appears in the distance. We carry on up the main valley to a water mill and a bridge, which we cross. The trail ascends the valley gradually, and when the valley splits we take the right hand fork up past the one house village of Yurutse. We camp just past Yurutse at the base of the Ganda La, our first pass.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 06:</strong><strong>&nbsp; Gandala-Base of GandaLa - Skiu (3400 mts) 7- 8 hrs walk. (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek .The trail is clear as it zig zags towards the pass. As we climb the views become more spectacular. Behind us Stok Kangri dominates the skyline. Finally we reach the top of the Ganda La (4,950m) decked with colourful prayer flags, and the views are worth all the effort. Ahead is the Zanskar Range and behind are the Stok Mountains. Far below in the valley are the fields of Shingo. As we descend keep an eye open for marmots and blue sheep, both of which seem to thrive in these desolate, high altitude spots. An easy descent of 2 hours, we arrive Shingo. From here a long descent through a wooden ravine to Skiu village, where the trail meets the Markha valley.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 07.</strong><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Skiu&nbsp; &ndash; Markha &ndash; ( 3800 mts)&nbsp; 8 - 9 hrs walk. (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek, today trek will be fairly long, but easy walk today, as we trek along the valley to Markha. The terrain along the valley is not demanding, so there is plenty of opportunity to admire the magnificent scenery. The colours of the barren mountains of Ladakh are truly spectacular, pastel pinks, blues and greens shine in the brilliant sunshine and change colour dramatically as the sun rises and sets. The trail crosses the Markha River a few times, and although bridges have been built there may be some water crossing involved. Beyond the settlement of Chalak there is an impressive line of chortens to ward off any evil spirits trying to enter the valley - yo&#39; Ghostbusters! A medieval fort on the hillside tell us that we have almost reached Markha. Markha is a large village, the there will be time to explore in the afternoon. our camp will be on the lush grazing flats just outside the village.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 08.&nbsp;</strong><strong> Markha - Thathungtse (4330 mts) &ndash; 5- 6 hrs walk. (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast&nbsp; within 45 minuts of walk we have to cross Markha river twice .Just beyond Markha the trail meets the Chacham Valley. Here is the Umlung gompa, set way above us on the cliff face. There is time to visit the monastery, which is the most important in the valley and is affiliated to Hemis. Continuing up the valley we walk through Umlung village to Hankar where there are more impressive fort ruins and a small gompa. From Hankar the trail turns off from the main valley and now follows the Nimaling stream to Thahungtse where we camp. We may be lucky and see wild sheep high up on the grazing areas above the campsite.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 09.</strong><strong>&nbsp; Thathungtse &ndash;Nimaling ( 4750 mts) 3 &ndash; 4 hrs walk. (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek, after the short walk to Nimaling. The trail climbs steeply to the plateau where the valley opens out. In this area there is no permanent habitation but during the summer months the shepherds bring their flocks of sheep, goats and dzos to graze on the high altitude pasture. The shepherds stay in stone shelters close to the grazing area for the whole summer, and we can often buy yoghurt or chang from them. Chang is a local beer brewed from barley and is an acquired taste...sorry, no Creemore beer available! In the evenings the animals are brought down from the hills and typical to have hundreds of them wandering through the campsite. We should have the afternoon in Nimaling.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 10.</strong><strong> Nimaling -Sumdo (3650mts) 8- 9hrs walk &amp; drive to Leh (B,L,D) </strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast start trek,&nbsp; the trail begins today by climbing to the Gongmaru La. It is a fairly long, steep ascent zig zagging to the top of the pass at 5,200m., but the views from the top are worth the effort. Looking back we see KangYangtse and Nun Kun in the far distance. Ahead there are views across the Stok Range and down to the Indus valley. The descent is steep at first to a tea tent, which is sometimes open for a welcome cup of tea. We then enter a spectacular gorge and descend gradually with a few small river crossings. High up on the barren cliffs we may spot the elusive Blue Sheep which inhabit this area. Passing through Shogdo we continue our descent to the village of Sumda. Rejoin our transport &amp; drive to Leh. Upon arrival check in hotel. Evening Dinner</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 11</strong>: <strong>Leh &ndash; Delhi &ndash; Final departure (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast, transfer to airport for your flight to Delhi. Upon arrival, meet and start tour around Delhi. Visit <strong>Indian Gate</strong>, <strong>President Palace and Red Ford</strong>. You will have lunch in the city center. Late after noon free time for shopping. You will have dinner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After dinner transfer to airport and connect flight back home. End of the service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1)&nbsp; Minimum 2 pax to travel </strong></p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Domestic air ticket with all the taxes</li>\r\n	<li>Inner line permit</li>\r\n	<li>All private transportation including airport transfers by Car/Jeep</li>\r\n	<li>English speaking tour guide throughout the trip</li>\r\n	<li>All the accommodation in Leh &ndash;A class standard (Local) hotels twin or triple sharing basis</li>\r\n	<li>All the meals as per itinerary</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Trek</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1 English speaking trekking guide, 3 assistant local guides</li>\r\n	<li>Full camping trek arrangement with:</li>\r\n	<li>Equipment: Two man tent, Dinning tent, Mattress and necessary cooking Utensils</li>\r\n	<li>Manpower: 1 Cook, 2 Kitchen helper and necessary porters/Horse</li>\r\n	<li>100 degree Boiled Drinking water during the trek</li>\r\n	<li>All the necessary&nbsp;trekking permit&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>International air ticket</li>\r\n	<li>India Visa (You can apply on your own country)</li>\r\n	<li>06 Nights hotel in Leh</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li>All alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>All personal expenses</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss, theft and damages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '11', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 0.00, 2300.00, '', '', NULL, NULL, 9, 1, 1, '0', '0', '1', '2016-08-08 10:55:41', '2016-08-08 16:37:40', NULL),
(76, 15, 7, '07 Days Explore Kashmir Tour', '07-days-explore-kashmir-tour', '07 Days Explore Kashmir Tour', '07 Days Explore Kashmir Tour', '07 Days Explore Kashmir Tour', '<p><strong>07 Days Explore Kashmir Tour</strong></p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Day 01:&nbsp;&nbsp; Singapore &ndash; Delhi&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\nDepart evening flight from Singapore, arrive Delhi late night. Meet and transfer to hotel. Overnight in Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 02:&nbsp; Delhi-Srinagar (1850m) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast transfer to&nbsp;domestic&nbsp;airport to take a short flight (1 hr) to Srinagar.&nbsp;Upon arrival Srinagar, transfer and check in to your deluxe Houseboat on Dal Lake.&nbsp;After lunch visit <strong>Moghul Gardens</strong>. The garden is a combination of three renowned gardens namely the <strong>Nishat Bagh, Shalimar Gardens and Chashmashahi.</strong> These gardens are beautifully decorated with bright flowerbeds, terraced lawns and well maintained cascading fountains. After that leisure stroll around the market and evening transfer to deluxe Houseboat. Dinner and overnight in the deluxe Houseboat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 03: Srinagar &ndash; Gulmarg (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nEarly morning enjoy the <strong>sunrise view over Dal Lake</strong> followed by breakfast in Houseboat.&nbsp; After that check out and drive to <strong>Gulmarg</strong> (1hr).We stop for a short break at Tangmarg&nbsp; and&nbsp;transfer to Gulmarg by 4wheel drive (45min) via the snow path route. Upon reaching Gulmarg check in Resort and lunch.&nbsp;After lunch visit <strong>Institute of Skiing and Mountaineering</strong>. Afternoon&nbsp; Rest &amp; Relax. Overnight at Resort.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 04:&nbsp; Gulmarg (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast, After breakfast enjoy the thrilling <strong>Gondola Ride</strong> and take in the superb <strong>Himalayan panorama including Nanga Parbat and some distant peaks</strong>. One of the highest Gondola Ride in the world. After the Ride back to Resort have lunch. Afternoon tour around the Gulmarg. Evening dinner and overnight at Resort.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 05:&nbsp; Gulmarg -Srinagar (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast check out and&nbsp; return to Srinagar. Stop at the Srinager city for lunch and some shopping around the city. After that transfer to Houseboat. &nbsp;Late afternoon enjoy a <strong>Shikara Ride on Dal Lake</strong>. Evening dinner and overnight indeluxe Houseboat.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 06:&nbsp; Srinagar &ndash; Delhi &ndash; Singapore (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast, transfer to airport for your flight to Delhi. Upon arrival, meet and start tour around Delhi. Visit <strong>Indian Gate</strong>, <strong>President Palace</strong> and <strong>Red Fort. </strong>For lunch, <strong>tuck into the Indian feast and the best tandoori chicken in town!</strong> Late afternoon free time for shopping followed by dinner.Transfer to airport and connect flight to Singapore.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 07: Arrive Singapore</strong><br />\r\nEarly morning arrive Singapore.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Minimum 2 persons to travel.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Domestic flight (Delhi &ndash; Srinagar- Delhi) with all the taxes</li>\r\n	<li>All private transportation including airport transfers as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>1 English speaking tour guide and tour escort as per itinerary throughout the trip</li>\r\n	<li>1 night 3 star standard&nbsp; hotel in twin or triple sharing basis</li>\r\n	<li>2 nights Deluxe houseboat in Srinagar on twin or triple sharing basis</li>\r\n	<li>2 nights ski resort in Gulmarg on twin or triple sharing basis</li>\r\n	<li>All the meals as per itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Shikara ride in Srinagar</li>\r\n	<li>All the entrances fees for places of visit</li>\r\n	<li>Gondola ride</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Return international air ticket</li>\r\n	<li>India visa (About SGD70)</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li>All alcoholic and other beverages</li>\r\n	<li>All personal expenses</li>\r\n	<li>Liabilities of loss, theft and damages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '7', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 0.00, 1400.00, 'Singapore', 'Singapore', NULL, NULL, 11, 1, NULL, '0', '0', '1', '2016-08-08 11:08:18', '2016-08-08 16:37:28', NULL),
(77, 15, 7, '8 Days Best of Kashmir Splendor', '8-days-best-of-kashmir-splendor', '8 Days Best of Kashmir Splendor', '8 Days Best of Kashmir Splendor', '8 Days Best of Kashmir Splendor', '<p>8 Days Best of Kashmir Splendor</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Delhi &ndash; Srinagar &ndash; Pahalgam &ndash; Gulmarg</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Day 1: Arrive &ndash; Delhi </strong><br />\r\nUpon arrival meet and transfer to hotel. Overnight in Delhi. Hotel</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 2: Delhi &ndash; Srinagar (1850m) (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast transfer to domestic airport to take a short flight (1 hr) to Srinagar. Upon arrival Srinagar, transfer and check in to your deluxe Houseboat on Dal Lake. After lunch visit Moghul Gardens. The garden is a combination of three renowned gardens namely the Nishat Bagh, Shalimar Gardens and Chashmashahi. These gardens are beautifully decorated with bright flowerbeds, terraced lawns and well maintained cascading fountains. After that leisure stroll around the market and evening transfer to deluxe Houseboat. Dinner and overnight in the deluxe houseboat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 3: Srinagar (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast enjoy a Shikara Ride on Dal Lake. After lunch visit Srinagar city and shopping. Evening dinner and overnight in deluxe houseboat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 4: Srinagar &ndash; Pahalgam (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nEarly morning enjoy the sunrise view over Dal Lake followed by breakfast in Houseboat. After that check out and drive to Pahalgam. Pahalgam is in Anantnag District. It is a popular tourist destination. Pahalgam is located at elevation of 8989 feet. The town of Pahalgam (Village of Shepherds) offers breathtaking views. One can just relax in the hotels or enjoy water rafting etc.Pahalgam is also the entry point for the famous Amarnath Cave, a holy site for Hindus. On the way visit the Avantipur Ruins &ndash; the 1100 year old temple dedicated to Lord Vishnu. Avantipur was founded by king Avantivarman. The site has two temples. The larger one, Shiva-Avantishvara, is marked by massive walls some half a mile beneath the town on the outskirts of village Jaubror. The subsidiary shrines are to the rear corner of the courtyard. But the complex has, over the years, lost its grandeur and has been reduced to ruins, though it is still visited by the devout.Upon arrival check in the hotel followed by hot lunch and rest. Late afternoon visit local market. Evening back to hotel and dinner.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 5: Pahalgam (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast, embark on an excursion to Chandanwadi (3288m) and Betaab Valley. Lunch will be served at the Pahalgam Hotel.&nbsp; Surrounded by snow-covered mountain peaks and dense pine and deodar forests, this valley is the mouth of River Sheshnag. After your tour and enjoy the evening at leisure. Have dinner and enjoy a comfortable overnight stay at your hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 6: Pahalgam &ndash; Gulmarg (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast check out and drive to Gulmarg. We stop for a short break at Tangmarg and transfer to Gulmarg by 4wheel drive (45min) via the snow path route. Upon reaching Gulmarg check in Resort and lunch. After lunch visit Institute of Skiing and Mountaineering. Afternoon rest &amp; relax. Overnight at Resort.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 7: Gulmarg (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast, After breakfast enjoy the thrilling Gondola Ride and take in the superb Himalayan panorama including Nanga Parbat and some distant peaks. One of the highest Gondola Ride in the world. After the Ride back to Resort have lunch. Afternoon tour around the Gulmarg. Evening dinner and overnight at Resort.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 8: Gulmarg &ndash; Srinagar &ndash; Delhi &ndash; Final Departure&nbsp; (B,L,D)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast check out and return to Srinagar airport and connect flight to Delhi. Upon arrival, meet and start tour around Delhi. Visit Indian Gate, President Palace and Red Fort. Late afternoon free time for shopping followed by dinner. Transfer to airport as per your flight.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Note:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1) Minimum 2 persons to travel.</p>\r\n', '<p>&bull;&nbsp; Domestic flight (Delhi &ndash; Srinagar- Delhi) with all the taxes<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp; All private transportation including airport transfers as per itinerary<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp; 1 English speaking tour guide and tour escort as per itinerary throughout the trip<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp; 1 night 3 star standard&nbsp; hotel in twin or triple sharing basis<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp; 2 nights Deluxe houseboat in Srinagar on twin or triple sharing basis<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp; 2 nights ski resort in Gulmarg on twin or triple sharing basis<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp; All the meals as per itinerary<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp; Shikara ride in Srinagar<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp; All the entrances fees for places of visit<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp; Gondola ride</p>\r\n', '<p>&bull;&nbsp; India visa (Pls apply your homeland country)<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp; Travel insurance<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp; All alcoholic and other beverages<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp; All personal expenses<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp; Liabilities of loss, theft and damages<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp; Tips</p>\r\n', '8', '', NULL, '', NULL, 0, 0, NULL, '', NULL, 0.00, 1500.00, 'Delhi', 'Delhi', NULL, NULL, 13, 1, 1, '0', '0', '1', '2016-08-08 11:21:15', '2016-08-08 16:37:28', NULL);

